{"title_page": "Yesterday Once More Tour", "text_new": "{{Infobox concert\n| concert_tour_name = Yesterday Once More Tour\n| image             = Official poster for the Yesterday Once More Tour by Dami Im.jpg\n| landscape         = \n| alt               = \n| caption           = \n| artist            = [[Dami Im]]\n| location          = [[Australia]]\n| type              = \n| album             = [[Classic Carpenters]]\n| start_date        = {{Start date|2016|07|01}}\n| end_date          = {{End date|2017|05|14}}\n| number_of_legs    = 2\n| number_of_shows   = 46\n| website           = \n| last_tour         = \n| this_tour         = Yesterday Once More Tour <br> (2016-17)\n| next_tour         = [[I Hear a Song Tour]] <br>(2018)\n| misc              = \n}}\n\nThe '''Yesterday Once More Tour''' is the first Australian national tour by Australia's [[2016 Eurovision Song Contest]] representative, and pop star, [[Dami Im]]. As a [[Korean Australians|Korean-Australian]] singer and songwriter, Dami was born in [[South Korea]], and emigrated to [[Australia]] with her family at the age of nine. Im won the [[The X Factor (Australia season 5)|fifth season]] of ''[[The X Factor (Australian TV series)|The X Factor Australia]]'' and subsequently received a recording contract with [[Sony Music Australia]].\n\n==Announcement==\nThe Tour was announced on 3 April 2016 and was carried by news and social media.<ref name=\"Tour\">{{cite web|url=http://www.damiim.com/dami-im-announces-yesterday-once-more-classic-carpenters-2016-tour/|publisher=www.damiim.com|date=2016-04-03|title=Dami Im Announces \u2018Yesterday Once More: Classic Carpenters\u2019 2016 Tour!}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://au.tv.yahoo.com/sunrise/a/31412338/dami-im-yesterday-once-more-classic-carpenters-tour-dates-and-ticketing-information/|author=Yahoo7 - Sunrise|publisher=au.tv.yahoo.com|date=2016-04-22|title=Dami Im \u2018Yesterday Once More\u2019 Classic Carpenters Tour Dates and Ticketing Information}}</ref>  The announcement of the Tour coincided with the announcement of the release of her cover album of [[the Carpenters]] aptly named ''[[Classic Carpenters]]'' on 22 April 2016. ''Classic Carpenters'' debuted at number three in the [[Australian Recording Industry Association|Australian ARIA Album Charts]] and #1 on the Australian Album Chart and #1 on the Physical Chart.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://sonymusic.com.au/news/dami-ims-album-classic-carpenters-debuts-1-aria-australian-album-chart/|author=Sony Music Australia|publisher=sonymusic.com.au|date=2016-05-02|title=Dami Im\u2019s Album \u2018Classic Carpenters\u2019 Debuts at #1 on ARIA Australian Album Chart!}}</ref> When it was first announced, the Tour was scheduled for 36 shows that traverse the whole of Australia, including many regional locations.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.auspop.com.au/2016/04/touring-dami-im/|author=auspOp|publisher=www.auspop.com.au|date=2016-04-04|title=TOURING : Dami Im}}</ref> Subsequently, due to the successful reception of the Tour, with many locations being sold out, some way ahead of schedule, two additional dates were added. Subsequently, on 13 September 2016, the \"Yesterday Once More Encore Tour\" was announced with additional dates and venues lined up between January and May 2017.<ref name=\"EncoreTour\">{{cite web|url=http://www.damiim.com/dami-im-announces-yesterday-2017-encore-tour/|publisher=www.damiim.com|date=2016-09-13|title=Dami Im Announces \u2018Yesterday Once More\u2019 2017 Encore Tour}}</ref>\n\n==Description==\nAs Im described it, the Tour was designed to be an intimate show that showcases the cover songs from her ''Classic Carpenters'' album, as well as her own hit singles, including her rousing Eurovision 2016 song \"[[Sound of Silence (Dami Im song)|Sound of Silence]]\". The set also includes several songs from her ''[[The X Factor (Australia season 3)|X Factor]]'' experience.\n\n==Reception==\n\n{{Empty section|date=December 2018}}\n\n==Band==\n[[File:Dami_Im_and_YOM_Tour_Band.jpg|thumb|right|Dami Im and her Yesterday Once More Tour Band]]\n\nDami Im's Yesterday Once More Band that accompanied her throughout the Tour consists of the following accomplished musicians:\n\n* [[Michael Tan (Dami Im YOM Band)|Michael Tan]] - Musical Director: Keyboards, Guitar and Violin\n* [[Adrian Veale]] - Trumpet, Flugel, Horn and Percussion\n* [[Kingsley Oldmeadow]] - Drums\n* [[Chris Travaglini]] - Guitar and Tenor Saxophone\n* [[Bobby Poulton]] - Bass, Upright Bass, Synthesiser and Backing Vocal\n* [[Izayah Mariner]] - Backing Vocal\n* [[Najla Michel]] - Backing Vocal\n\n==Set list==\n* This is the set list from November dates.\n\n# \"[[There's a Kind of Hush]]\" \n# \"[[Yesterday Once More (song)|Yesterday Once More]]\" \n# \"[[I Won't Last a Day Without You]]\" \n# \"[[Top of the World (The Carpenters song)|Top of the World]]\" \n# \"[[Hurting Each Other]]\" \n# \"[[I Need to Be in Love]]\" \n# \"[[Bridge Over Troubled Water]]\" \n# \"[[Alive (Dami Im song)|Alive]]\" \n# \"[[Don't Leave Me This Way]]\" \n# \"[[Super Love (Dami Im song)|Super Love]]\" \n# \"[[Rainy Days and Mondays]]\" \n# \"[[A Song for You]]\" \n# \"[[Gladiator (Dami Im song)|Gladiator]]\" \n# \"[[Jolene (song)|Jolene]]\" \n# \"[[Smile (Dami Im song)|Smile]]\" \n# \"[[Superstar (Carpenters song)|Superstar]]\" \n# \"[[Purple Rain (song)|Purple Rain]]\" \n# \"He Knows My Name\" \n# \"[[We've Only Just Begun]]\" \n# \"[[Fighting for Love (song)|Fighting for Love]]\" \n# \"[[Sound of Silence (Dami Im song)|Sound of Silence]]\" \n# \"[[(They Long to Be) Close to You]]\"\n\n==Tour dates==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n! width=\"150\"| Date<ref name=\"Tour\"/><ref name=\"EncoreTour\"/><ref>{{cite web|author=Bandsintown|url=http://www.bandsintown.com/DamiIm|title=Dami Im Tour Dates|publisher=www.bandsintown.com}}</ref><ref>http://www.damiim.com/tour/</ref>\n! width=\"150\"| City\n! width=\"150\"| Country\n! width=\"250\"| Venue\n|-\n|1 July 2016\n|[[Frankston, Victoria|Frankston]]\n|rowspan=\"38\"|[[Australia]]\n|[[Frankston Arts Centre]]\n|-\n|2 July 2016\n|[[Geelong]]\n|[[Geelong Performing Arts Centre]]\n|-\n|15 July 2016\n|[[Wollongong]]\n|[[Illawarra Performing Arts Centre]]\n|-\n|16 July 2016\n|[[Canberra]]\n|[[Canberra Theatre]]\n|-\n|22 July 2016\n|[[Chatswood, New South Wales|Chatswood]]\n|[[The Concourse, Chatswood|Concourse Theatre]]\n|-\n|23 July 2016\n|[[Revesby, New South Wales|Revesby]]\n|[[Revesby Workers Club]]\n|-\n|29 July 2016\n|[[Dee Why]]\n|[[Dee Why RSL]]\n|-\n|30 July 2016\n|[[Rooty Hill]]\n|[[Rooty Hill RSL]]\n|-\n|5 August 2016\n|[[Mount Pritchard]]\n|[[Mounties]]\n|-\n|6 August 2016\n|[[Wagga Wagga]]\n|[[Wagga Wagga Civic Theatre|The Civic Theatre]]\n|-\n|12 August 2016\n|[[Merimbula]]\n|[[Club Sapphire]]\n|-\n|13 August 2016\n|[[Currarong]]\n|[[Shoalhaven Entertainment Centre]]\n|-\n|19 August 2016\n|[[Sydney]]\n|[[South Sydney Juniors Club]]\n|-\n|20 August 2016\n|[[Castle Hill, New South Wales|Castle Hill]]\n|[[Castle Hill RSL]]\n|-\n|27 August 2016\n|[[Newcastle, Australia|Newcastle]]\n|[[Belmont 16\u2019s]]\n|-\n|9 September 2016\n|[[Hurstville]]\n|[[Club Central]]\n|-\n|10 September 2016\n|[[Cammeray]]\n|[[North Sydney Leagues]]\n|-\n|17 September 2016\n|[[Campbelltown, New South Wales|Campbelltown]]\n|[[The Cube (Sydney)|The Cube]]\n|-\n|18 September 2016\n|[[North Gosford]]\n|[[Laycock Street Theatre]]\n|-\n|7 October 2016\n|[[Orange, Australia|Orange]]\n|[[Orange Ex Services]]\n|-\n|8 October 2016\n|[[Dubbo]]\n|[[Dubbo RSL]]\n|-\n|14 October 2016\n|[[Hobart]]\n|[[Wrest Point Hotel Casino|Wrest Point Entertainment Centre]]\n|-\n|15 October 2016\n|[[Prospect Vale, Tasmania|Prospect Vale]]\n|[[Country Club Casino|Launceston Country Club]]\n|-\n|21 October 2016\n|[[Burwood, New South Wales|Burwood]]\n|[[Club Burwood]]\n|-\n|22 October 2016\n|[[Wentworthville]]\n|[[Wenty Leagues]]\n|-\n|3 November 2016{{efn|name=\"Aug05\"|Shows on 3 November 2016 and 3 December 2016 were added to the 