{"title_page": "Halsey (singer)", "text_new": "{{pp-vandalism|small=yes}}\n{{short description|American singer and songwriter}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=November 2019}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Halsey\n| image              = Halsey 2019 by Glenn Francis.jpg\n| caption            = Halsey at the [[2019 iHeartRadio Music Awards]]\n| birth_name         = Ashley Nicolette Frangipane\n| birth_date         = {{nowrap|{{birth date and age|1994|09|29}}}}\n| birth_place        = [[Edison, New Jersey]], [[United States|U.S.]]\n| residence          = [[Los Angeles]], [[California]], U.S.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://observer.com/2017/06/halsey-buys-house-beachwood-canyon-los-angeles/|title=Halsey Has the Perfect New House to Celebrate Her Album In|date=June 15, 2017}}</ref>\n| occupation         = {{flatlist|<!---occupation(s) artist is notable, \"as given in the lead\", per: [[Template:Infobox_person#Parameters]]--> \n* Singer\n* songwriter\n}}\n| years_active       = 2012\u2013present\n| home_town          = \n| awards             =\n| module             = {{Infobox musical artist|embed=yes\n| background       = solo_singer\n| instrument       = Vocals <!-- only for instrument(s) artist is primarily notable for using, per [[Template:Infobox_musical_artist/doc#instrument]]; \"The instruments infobox parameter is not intended as a WP:COATRACK for every instrument the subject has ever used\"-->\n| genre            = {{flatlist|<!--Aim for generality and use two to four genres: [[Template:Infobox_musical_artist/doc#genre]]-->\n* [[Pop music|Pop]]\n* [[electropop]]\n* [[synth-pop]]\n* [[alternative pop]]\n}}\n| label            = {{flatlist|\n* [[Capitol Records|Capitol]]\n* [[Virgin EMI Records|Virgin EMI]]\n* [[Astralwerks]]\n}}\n| associated_acts =\n| website         = {{URL|iamhalsey.com}}\n}}\n}}\n\n'''Ashley Nicolette Frangipane''' ({{IPAc-en|\u02cc|f|r|\u00e6|n|d\u0292|\u026a|'|p|\u0251\u02d0|n|i}} {{respell|FRAN|jih|PAH|nee}};<ref>{{YouTube|OdH6PC9SPLI|\"Halsey Tells Us How To Pronounce Her Last Name & Singing w/ Katy Perry. Part 1\"}}</ref>{{efn|{{IPA-it|\u02ccfrand\u0292i\u02c8pa\u02d0ne|lang}} {{respell|FRAN|jih|PAH|nay}}}} born September 29, 1994), known professionally as '''Halsey''' ({{IPAc-en|'|h|\u0254\u02d0|l|z|i}} {{respell|HAWL|zee}}),<ref name=\"kids\">{{cite web|title=Kids Interview Bands \u2013 Halsey|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Hw3fAn0S_KE |publisher=YouTube |date=October 13, 2014}}</ref> is an American singer and songwriter.<!--only occupations integral to artist's notability per reliable sources--> Gaining attention from self-released music on social media platforms, she was signed by [[Astralwerks]] in 2014 and released her debut [[EP (music)|EP]], ''[[Room 93]]'', later that year.\n\nHalsey has since earned one number-one album on the [[Billboard 200|''Billboard'' 200]] with ''[[Hopeless Fountain Kingdom]]'' (2017), as well as two number-two albums with [[Badlands (Halsey album)|''Badlands'']] (2015) and [[Manic (album)|''Manic'']] (2020). She has earned two number-one singles on the [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]], including \"[[Closer (Chainsmokers song)|Closer]]\", a collaboration with [[The Chainsmokers]], and \"[[Without Me (Halsey song)|Without Me]]\"; she has also attained a top-five single with \"[[Bad at Love]]\". In total, Halsey has sold over one million albums and has been streamed over six billion times in the United States.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/business/chart-beat/8549032/halsey-album-sales-most-streamed-songs-ask-billboard-mailbag|title=Halsey's Album Sales & Most-Streamed Songs, From 'Closer' to 'Without Me' & More: Ask Billboard Mailbag|website=Billboard|access-date=2020-01-27}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/business/chart-beat/8549077/eminem-scores-10th-no-1-album-billboard-200-chart-music-to-be-murdered-by|title=Eminem Scores Historic 10th No. 1 Album on Billboard 200 Chart With 'Music to Be Murdered By'|website=Billboard|access-date=2020-01-27}}</ref> All three of her studio albums have been supported by a headlining tour.\n\nHalsey is noted for her distinctive singing voice.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://wixx.com/news/articles/2018/jul/27/halsey-says-using-her-weird-voice-to-play-wonder-woman-in-teen-titans-go-to-the-movies-is-her-calling/|title=Halsey says using her \"weird voice\" to play Wonder Woman in \"Teen Titans Go! to the Movies\" is \"her calling\"|last=Inc|first=Midwest Communications|website=101 WIXX|access-date=2020-01-27}}</ref> Her awards and nominations include four [[Billboard Music Award|''Billboard'' Music Awards]], one [[American Music Awards|American Music Award]], one [[GLAAD Media Award]], three [[Guinness World Records|''Guinness'' World Records]], an [[2019 MTV Video Music Awards|MTV Video Music Award]] and two [[Grammy Award]] nominations. Outside of her career, she has been involved in [[suicide prevention]] awareness and [[sexual assault]] victim advocacy.\n\n== Early life ==\nAshley Nicolette Frangipane was born on September 29, 1994, in [[Edison, New Jersey]].<ref name=NJOlivier>{{cite web |date=October 15, 2017 |first=Bobby |last=Olivier |url=http://www.nj.com/entertainment/music/index.ssf/2017/10/halsey_concert_review_2017_hopeless_nj_prudential.html | title= N.J. pop star Halsey was magnetic in her largest home-state concert yet |website=NJ.com |language=en-US |access-date=October 16, 2017 }}</ref> Her parents dropped out of college after her mother discovered that she was pregnant with her.<ref name=\"Morris2016\">{{Cite news |last=Morris |first= Alex |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/features/inside-halseys-troubled-past-chaotic-present-w431261 |title=Inside Halsey's Troubled Past, Chaotic Present |date=July 28, 2016 |work=Rolling Stone |access-date=March 8, 2017}}</ref> Her mother, Nicole, works for security in a hospital, and her father, Chris, manages a car dealership.<ref>Lustig, Jay. [http://archive.northjersey.com/news/concert-review-halsey-at-madison-square-garden-1.1645420 \"Concert review: Halsey at Madison Square Garden\"] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161220170216/http://archive.northjersey.com/news/concert-review-halsey-at-madison-square-garden-1.1645420 |date=December 20, 2016 }}, ''[[The Record (Bergen County)]]'', August 14, 2016. Accessed December 9, 2016. \"Halsey \u2013 who grew up as Ashley Frangipane in Clark, and is now 21 \u2013 wiped a tear from her eye as she told the story, standing on the Garden's stage herself, Saturday night.\"</ref><ref name=\"billboard.com\">{{cite web|last1=Ringen|first1=Jonathan|title=Billboard Cover: How Halsey Became the Voice of Her Generation Through Tweets, Tumblr and Truth-Telling|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/cover-story/6971430/billboard-cover-halsey-on-fans-fame-music-success|website=Billboard.com|publisher=Billboard-Hollywood Reporter Media Group|accessdate=February 4, 2017}}</ref> Nicole is of [[Italians|Italian]], [[Hungarians|Hungarian]], and [[Irish people|Irish]] descent, while Chris is [[African Americans|African-American]] with some Irish ancestry.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://twitter.com/halsey/status/457944268821512194|title=h on Twitter|work=Twitter|access-date=May 16, 2017|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.paradigmagency.com/music/artists/halsey/ | title=Halsey\u2013A biography | publisher=Paradigm Talent Agency | accessdate=April 1, 2015}}</ref> Frangipane has two younger brothers, Sevian and Dante.<ref name=\"Morris2016\" /> She played the violin, viola, and cello, until moving on to the acoustic guitar when she was 14 years old.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.paradigmagency.com/music/artists/halsey/|title=Halsey - Paradigm Talent Agency|website=paradigmagency.com|access-date=February 27, 2019}}</ref>\n\nThroughout her childhood Frangipane's family moved frequently, as her parents worked many jobs. By the time she reached her teen years she had enrolled in six schools.<ref name=\":4\">{{cite magazine|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/6671107/halsey-the-weeknd-drugs-badlands-billboard-feature|title=Art-Pop Singer Halsey on Being Bipolar, Bisexual and an 'Inconvenient Woman'|magazine=Billboard}}</ref> In high school, Frangipane endured bullying by other students,<ref name=\"billboard.com\" /><ref name=\"Gomez\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.thelist.com/132005/the-untold-truth-of-halsey/|title=The untold truth of Halsey|last=Gomez|first=Luis|website=TheList.com|language=en-US|access-date=February 28, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.altpress.com/news/halsey-panic-at-the-disco-bullying/|title=Brendon Urie had an amazing response to Halsey being bullied at school|date=October 9, 2018|website=Alternative Press|language=en-US|access-date=February 28, 2019}}</ref> and at 17 she attempted suicide, which led to a 17-day hospitalization. Following this, she was diagnosed as [[Bipolar disorder|bipolar]]; her mother also struggles with the disorder.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.refinery29.com/en-us/2018/07/204397/halsey-bipolar-mental-illness-interview|title=Halsey Opens Up About Juggling Her Career & Bipolar Disorder|last=Fredette|first=Meagan|website=refinery29.com|language=en|date=July 15, 2018|access-date=December 23, 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"NylonOpens\">{{Cite web|url=https://nylon.com/articles/halsey-opens-up-about-being-bipolar|title=Halsey Talks About Her Bipolar Disorder|last=Gharnit|first=Yasmeen|date=May 28, 2015|website=[[Nylon (magazine)|Nylon]]|language=en|access-date=December 23, 2018}}</ref> She began using recreational drugs soon after, claiming her bipolar disorder caused her to become an \"unconventional child\".<ref name=\":4\" /> Also, when she was 17, she became romantically involved with a man who was 24 and lived on the [[Halsey Street (BMT Canarsie Line)|Halsey Street]] in Brooklyn. Frangipane said, \"That's where I first starting writing music and where I started to feel like I was a part of something bigger than my town in middle of nowhere [[New Jersey]]. Halsey is kind of like a manifestation of all the exaggerated parts of me, so it's like an alter ego.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://hollywoodlife.com/2018/05/22/who-is-halsey-singer/|title=Halsey: 5 Things To Know About Singer Hitting The Stage For 'The Voice' Finale|last=Brow|first=Jason|date=May 22, 2018|website=Hollywood Life|language=en|access-date=January 12, 2019}}</ref> In 2012, she graduated from [[Warren Hills Regional High School]] in [[Washington, New Jersey]].<ref>Buffum, Joanna; and Kortebein. [https://njmonthly.com/articles/arts-entertainment/fetty-wap-halsey-charlie-puth-nj-pop-heavyweights/ \"Fetty Wap, Halsey & Charlie Puth: New Jersey's Young Pop Heavyweights; Three New Jersey musicians are dominating the pop charts and breaking records\u2014and they were all born in the '90s.\"], ''[[New Jersey Monthly]]'', October 30, 2015. Accessed February 8, 2018. \"Halsey; Hometown: Washington... She graduated from Warren Hills Regional High School in 2012 and worked on songwriting until she self-released her first single, 'Ghost', on SoundCloud in January 2014.\"</ref>\n\nAfter graduating, Frangipane enrolled in the [[Rhode Island School of Design]]; however, she withdrew due to financial hardship and attended community college instead.<ref name=\"Morris2016\" /> She eventually dropped out of community college and was ejected from her home, saying, \"They just didn't agree with a lot of things about me\". Soon after, she lived in a basement in lower [[Manhattan]] with a group of \"degenerate stoners\" whom she knew through her then-boyfriend.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://time.com/4429627/halsey-rolling-stone-interview/|title=Halsey Opened Up to 'Rolling Stone' About Her Life|website=Time|language=en|access-date=December 23, 2018}}</ref> When she was not living there, she occasionally lived in one of New York's many homeless shelters, and she considered [[prostitution]] as a way to make money.<ref name=VultureMeans>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vulture.com/2017/06/what-it-means-to-be-halsey.html|title=What it Means to Be Halsey|last=Reilly|first=Phoebe|date=June 2017|website=Vulture|access-date=October 29, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.foxnews.com/entertainment/halsey-considered-prostitution-sex-work-before-she-got-a-record-deal|title=Halsey considered prostitution, sex work before she got a record deal|last=Sager|first=Jessica|date=April 8, 2019|website=Fox News|language=en-US|access-date=April 15, 2019}}</ref> When describing this period of her life, Frangipane said, \"I remember one time I had $9 in my bank account, and bought a four-pack of Red Bull and used it to stay up overnight over the course of two or three days, because it was less dangerous to not sleep than it was to sleep somewhere random and maybe get raped or kidnapped.\" She would occasionally stay with her maternal grandmother.<ref name=\"Morris2016\" />\n\n==Career==\n=== 2012\u20132014: Career beginnings ===\nFrangipane started writing music when she was 17, and in 2012 she began posting videos to social media sites such as [[YouTube]] and [[Kik Messenger|Kik]], and in particular [[Tumblr]], under the username of ''se7enteenblack''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/2618129/thank-you-halsey-fangirl/|title=Thank You, Halsey, For Being A Fangirl Just Like Me|last=Lakshmin|first=Deepa|website=MTV News|language=en|access-date=December 23, 2018}}</ref> She became known for a parody of [[Taylor Swift]]'s song \"[[I Knew You Were Trouble]]\", inspired by Swift's relationship with [[Harry Styles]]. She then wrote a follow up song about their relationship which was posted online in early 2013.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://popcrush.com/halsey-haylor-song-sos-listen/ | title=Halsey used to write songs about Taylor Swift + Harry Styles | work=Popcrush | accessdate=October 27, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.girlfriend.com.au/how-halsey-became-famous|title=The way Halsey became famous is totally weird and crazy and we had NO idea|website=girlfriend.com.au|language=en-us|access-date=December 23, 2018}}</ref> In early 2014, Frangipane went to a party and met a \"music guy\" who asked her to collaborate on a song with him because he liked her voice. The result, a song about her ex-boyfriend titled \"[[Ghost (Halsey song)|Ghost]]\", was posted by Frangipane on [[SoundCloud]] several weeks after it was recorded. Within hours, the song gained online popularity, and she was subsequently contacted by several record labels, with the song eventually charting and going on radio. She signed with [[Astralwerks]], feeling that they gave her more creative freedom than other labels that contacted her.<ref name=\"Morris2016\" />\n\nFollowing this, Frangipane played numerous acoustic shows in different cities under several [[stage name]]s.<ref name=\"Hurricane\">{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop-shop/6288853/halsey-hurricane-video-premiere|title=Exclusive Premiere: Watch Singer-Songwriter's Halsey's Gritty 'Hurricane' Video From Her Visual 'Room 93' EP|last1=Leight|first1=Elias|date=October 16, 2014|website=Billboard|access-date=}}</ref> She chose Halsey as her permanent stage name because it is an [[anagram]] of her first name, and is also a reference to the Halsey Street station of the [[New York City Subway]] in [[Brooklyn]],{{efn|Halsey's name can be based on either the [[Halsey Street (BMT Canarsie Line)|station]] on the {{NYCS trains|Canarsie|time=nolink}}, the [[Halsey Street (BMT Jamaica Line)|station]] on the {{NYCS trains|Jamaica east J|time=nolink}}, or both. In a ''[[Rolling Stone]]'' interview, Halsey did not clarify which station she based her name on.<ref name=\"Morris2016\" />}} a place she spent a lot of time at when she was a teenager.<ref name=\"dscvr\">{{cite web|last1=Vevo|title=Halsey \u2013 dscvr Interview|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=cUG8VDYy7CY|website=Youtube|date=January 19, 2015}}</ref> She also stated Halsey was the most popular name she used.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.celebuzz.com/2016-03-28/9-facts-about-halsey/|title=9 Facts That You Should Know About Rising Star, Halsey|date=March 28, 2016|website=Celebuzz|language=en-US|access-date=December 23, 2018}}</ref> Having written poems for years, Halsey began writing more serious songs as a way to promote them. Music became Halsey's \"confessional approach\" and a form of therapy after the difficult life she had endured.<ref name=\"Morris2016\" />\n\n=== 2014\u20132016: ''Badlands'' and breakthrough ===\n[[File:Halsey LA (3).PNG|thumb|upright|Halsey performing in Los Angeles in 2015.]]\nHalsey began touring with [[The Kooks]] in August 2014 and performed various original songs.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.allthingsgomusic.com/interview-halsey/|title=Interview: Halsey|work=allthingsgomusic.com|accessdate=March 31, 2015}}</ref> She released her debut extended play, ''[[Room 93]]'', on October 27, 2014.<ref name=\"Astralwerks\">{{cite web|url=http://www.astralwerks.com/news/halsey-signs-to-astralwerks-with-debut-single-ghost/|title=Halsey Signs to Astralwerks with Debut Single \"Ghost\"|date=August 7, 2014|website=Astralwerks|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150325024144/http://www.astralwerks.com/news/halsey-signs-to-astralwerks-with-debut-single-ghost/|archivedate=March 25, 2015|url-status=dead}}</ref> The EP charted in the lower regions of the US [[Billboard 200|''Billboard'' 200]] and at number three on the [[Top Heatseekers]] chart.<ref name=\"autogenerated1\">{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/halsey|title=Halsey|website=Billboard}}</ref> She then began work on her debut studio album and performed songs from the upcoming album at [[South by Southwest]] in 2015, where she was the most tweeted about performer of the night.<ref name=\"sxsw\">{{cite web|author1=Andrew Flanagan|title=Halsey, Run The Jewels & Miley Top Twitter's Most-Shared During SXSW|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/events/festivals/6509472/sxsw-twitter-stats-miley-cyrus-run-the-jewels|website=Billboard|accessdate=April 2, 2015|date=March 23, 2015}}</ref> She embarked on a co-headlining tour with [[Young Rising Sons]] in March, and in June, she became the opening act for [[Imagine Dragons]] on their [[Smoke + Mirrors Tour]] (2015) during the North American leg.<ref name=\":7\">{{cite web|last1=Gonzalez|first1=Ross \"Taco\"|title=Halsey and Young Rising Sons announce a co-headlining tour|url=http://www.thenetwork317.net/halsey-and-young-rising-sons-announce-a-co-headlining-tour/|website=The Network 317|date=January 12, 2015}}</ref>\n\nHalsey's debut studio album, [[Badlands (Halsey album)|''Badlands'']], was released on August 28, 2015. She described ''Badlands'' as a [[concept album]] about a [[dystopia|dystopian future society]] known as \"The Badlands\", which was a metaphor for her mental state at the time, stating that each song meant something different to her.<ref name=\"KROQ\">{{cite interview|author=Halsey|title=Halsey Interview With Shelley Rome|url=http://www.z100.com/media/podcast-shelley-rome-interviews-shelleyrome/halsey-interview-with-shelley-rome-26337386/|publisher=WHTZ|location=New York City, New York|date=September 9, 2015|others=Shelley Rome|access-date=July 5, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151002045425/http://www.z100.com/media/podcast-shelley-rome-interviews-shelleyrome/halsey-interview-with-shelley-rome-26337386/|archive-date=October 2, 2015|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-lists/10-new-artists-you-need-to-know-august-2015-14574/|title=10 New Artists You Need to Know: August 2015|date=August 17, 2015|website=Rolling Stone|language=en-US|access-date=January 25, 2019}}</ref> Halsey wrote all of the songs on the album when she was 19, while production was handled by a number of producers, including then boyfriend, Norwegian producer [[Lido (musician)|Lido]].<ref>{{cite magazine|url=http://www.complex.com/music/2015/07/interview-halsey-new-album-badlands|title=Halsey Talks Her New Album, 'Badlands'|last=Morris|first=Jessie|date=July 10, 2015|magazine=Complex|accessdate=August 29, 2015}}</ref> The album was described by Halsey as not having a \"proper radio hit\".<ref name=\"VultureMeans\" /> It received positive reviews from music critics,<ref name=\"AM Review\">{{cite web|url=https://www.allmusic.com/album/badlands-mw0002860377|title=Badlands \u2013 Halsey|last=Collar|first=Matt|website=[[AllMusic]]|accessdate=September 29, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.alternativeaddiction.com/Review/503|title=Alternative Addiction {{!}} Review of Halsey \"Badlands\" {{!}} Alternative Addiction - New Music|website=alternativeaddiction.com|access-date=February 27, 2019}}</ref> with Joe Levy of ''[[Rolling Stone (magazine)|Rolling Stone]]'' citing Halsey as a \"new Tumblr popstar with a knack for sticky imagery\".<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/albumreviews/halsey-badlands-20150828|title=Halsey 'Badlands' Album Review|work=Rolling Stone|access-date=April 7, 2018}}</ref> ''Badlands'' debuted at number two on the Billboard 200 albums chart in the US, selling 115,000 copies in its first week, of which 97,000 were pure album sales.<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/6685947/the-weeknd-beauty-behind-the-madness-debuts-at-no-1-billboard-200-charts|title=Halsey's \"Badlands\" Debuts at #2 on the Billboard 200 Albums Chart|magazine=Billboard.com|accessdate=September 7, 2015}}</ref> The album found success in several other countries, including Australia, Canada, and New Zealand, where the album debuted in the top three.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://australian-charts.com/showitem.asp?interpret=Halsey&titel=Badlands&cat=a|title=australian-charts.com - Halsey - Badlands|website=australian-charts.com|access-date=June 12, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/halsey|title=Halsey Chart History|website=Billboard|access-date=June 12, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://charts.nz/showitem.asp?interpret=Halsey&titel=Badlands&cat=a|title=charts.nz - Halsey - Badlands|website=charts.nz|access-date=June 12, 2019}}</ref> It was further promoted by Halsey's [[Badlands Tour]] (2015\u201316), and her spot as the opening act for select dates of [[The Weeknd]]'s [[The Madness Fall Tour]] (2015).<ref>{{cite news|url=http://music.mxdwn.com/2015/10/24/news/halsey-announces-madison-square-garden-show-for-the-2016-time-warner-cable-concert-series/|title=Halsey Announces Madison Square Garden Show For The 2016 Time Warner Cable Concert Series|last1=Morecraft|first1=Shannon|date=October 24, 2015|accessdate=January 12, 2016|publisher=MXDWN}}</ref>\n\n''Badlands'' was certified Platinum by the [[Recording Industry Association of America]] (RIAA) for U.S. sales of 1,000,000 units.<ref name=\":8\">{{Cite news|url=https://celebmix.com/badlands-goes-platinum-in-the-usa/|title=Halsey's Album 'Badlands' Goes Platinum In The USA|date=September 8, 2016|work=CelebMix|access-date=April 7, 2018|language=en-GB}}</ref> Four singles were released from the album: \"[[Ghost (Halsey song)|Ghost]]\", \"[[New Americana]]\", \"[[Colors (Halsey song)|Colors]]\", and \"[[Castle (Halsey song)|Castle]]\", all of which were certified Platinum in the US.<ref name=\":9\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.riaa.com/gold-platinum/|title=Gold & Platinum|website=RIAA|language=en-US|access-date=March 24, 2019}}</ref> The latter three singles achieved minor commercial success; \"New Americana\" reached number 60 on the US [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/halsey|title=Halsey Chart History|website=Billboard|access-date=March 24, 2019}}</ref> \"Colors\" became the album's most streamed track on [[Spotify]] and was certified Silver in the UK,<ref name=\":22\">{{Cite web|url=https://chartmasters.org/2019/03/streaming-masters-halsey/|title=Streaming Masters - Halsey|last=Blanchard|first=Anthony|date=March 1, 2019|website=ChartMasters|language=en-US|access-date=June 2, 2019}}</ref> and \"Castle\" was rerecorded for the soundtrack of the 2016 film ''[[The Huntsman: Winter's War]].''<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/watch-halseys-elegant-castle-the-huntsman-winters-war-version-video-224538/|title=Watch Halsey's 'Castle (The Huntsman: Winter's War)' Video|last=Legaspi|first=Althea|last2=Legaspi|first2=Althea|date=April 14, 2016|website=Rolling Stone|language=en-US|access-date=March 24, 2019}}</ref> \"[[Gasoline (Halsey song)|Gasoline]]\" was not released as a single and was only included on the deluxe version of ''Badlands'', but became one of the album's most popular tracks; it is the album's third most streamed track on Spotify,<ref name=\":22\" /> and was certified Platinum in the US.<ref name=\":9\" />\n\n[[File:Halsey Grammy Museum 2016 (27256690335).jpg|thumb|left|upright|Halsey performing at [[Grammy Museum at L.A. Live|The GRAMMY Museum]] in 2016]]\nHalsey was featured on the song \"The Feeling\" by [[Justin Bieber]] for his fourth studio album, ''[[Purpose (Justin Bieber album)|Purpose]]'' (2015).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.idolator.com/7613089/justin-bieber-purpose-kanye-west-halsey-the-feeling-skrillex|title=Justin Bieber Announces 'Purpose' Has A Halsey Collab, Confirms Kanye West's Involvement |first=Carl |last=Williott |date=October 28, 2015|website=[[Idolator (website)|Idolator]] (blog site) |accessdate=January 27, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop-shop/6745178/halsey-justin-bieber-purpose-the-feeling|title=Halsey & Justin Bieber Duet on Skrillex-Produced Track 'The Feeling' on 'Purpose'|website=Billboard.com|accessdate=January 27, 2018}}</ref> The song was not officially released, though entered the top forty of the ''Billboard'' Hot 100 and was certified Gold in the US and Silver in the UK.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bpi.co.uk/certified-awards/search.aspx|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130331041236/http://www.bpi.co.uk/certified-awards/search.aspx|url-status=dead|archive-date=March 31, 2013|title=Certified Awards|date=March 31, 2013|publisher=}}</ref> In February 2016, she was one of four female performers to partner with [[MAC cosmetics]] for their Future Forward line; Halsey released a lipstick named after herself.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.teenvogue.com/story/mac-halsey-tinashe-lion-babe-dej-loaf|title=This Might Be the Most Epic MAC Collaboration Ever|first=Sue|last=Williamson|website=Teenvogue.com|accessdate=January 27, 2018}}</ref> The Senior Vice President and Group Creative Director of the company, James Gager, said \"It feels like a great thing to be able to support artists who are breaking through but aren't necessarily at the top top, to push them forward.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/6866927/halsey-tinashe-lion-babe-dej-loaf-mac-cosmetics-future-forward|title=Halsey, Tinashe, Lion Babe and Dej Loaf To Front M\u00b7A\u00b7C Cosmetics Future Forward Campaign (Exclusive)|website=Billboard.com|accessdate=January 27, 2018}}</ref> In May 2016, Halsey released the song \"Tokyo Narita (Freestyle)\", produced by Lido.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://uk.complex.com/music/2016/05/halsey-and-lido-new-song-tokyo-narita-freestyle|title=Halsey And Lido Link Up For New Surprise Track, \"Tokyo Narita (Freestyle)\"|website=Complex UK|access-date=September 10, 2016}}</ref><ref name=\":23\">{{cite web|url=http://www.thefader.com/2016/05/20/halsey-tokyo-narita-freestyle|title=Halsey Returns With The \"Tokyo Narita Freestyle\"|website=The FADER|access-date=September 10, 2016}}</ref> The song was a standalone track that served as a promotional single from Halsey.<ref name=\":23\" /> In July 2016, Halsey collaborated with 26 other artists for the [[Charity record|charity single]] \"[[Hands (2016 song)|Hands]]\", which was a tribute for the victims of the [[Orlando nightclub shooting|Pulse nightclub shooting]].<ref name=\":19\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/7424145/britney-spears-pink-selena-gomez-hands-orlando|title=Britney Spears, Pink, Selena Gomez Join 'Hands' for Orlando: How the All-Star Song Came to Life|website=Billboard|access-date=February 27, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\":20\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.popbuzz.com/music/artists/troye-sivan/news/troye-sivan-halsey-orlando-charity-single/|title=LISTEN: Troye Sivan, Halsey, And Others Team Up For Orlando Victims Charity Single|website=PopBuzz|language=en|access-date=March 6, 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn July 29, 2016, Halsey was featured as a vocalist on [[The Chainsmokers]]' single \"[[Closer (The Chainsmokers song)|Closer]],\" a song she also cowrote.<ref name=\"Fekadu\">{{cite web|last1=Fekadu|first1=Mesfin|title=2 Fray members get writing credit on Chainsmokers' No.1 hit|url=http://bigstory.ap.org/article/af7828bbf3d041aeaec60e5510218843/2-fray-members-get-writing-credit-chainsmokers-no1-hit|website=[[Associated Press]]|accessdate=September 3, 2016|date=September 2, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.teenvogue.com/story/the-chainsmokers-interview-halsey-debut-album|title=The Chainsmokers Get Real About Their Debut Album|last=Nast|first=Cond\u00e9|website=Teen Vogue|language=en|access-date=March 27, 2019}}</ref> The song achieved major commercial success; it topped the ''Billboard'' Hot 100 for 12 consecutive weeks, topped the charts of 12 other countries, sold more than 15 million units worldwide, and is one of [[Most streamed songs|most streamed songs on Spotify]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/drake-ed-sheeran-eminem-spotify-735527/|title=Drake, Ed Sheeran and Eminem Are Spotify's Biggest Artists Ever|last=Wang|first=Amy X.|last2=Wang|first2=Amy X.|date=October 10, 2018|website=Rolling Stone|language=en-US|access-date=March 24, 2019}}</ref> The official lyric video for \"Closer\" was released on [[YouTube]] on July 29, 2016, and has since garnered over two billion views.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=PT2_F-1esPk|title=The Chainsmokers - Closer ft. Halsey (Official Lyric Video)|last=ChainsmokersVEVO|date=|publisher=|accessdate=January 30, 2019|via=YouTube}}</ref> [[Billboard (magazine)|''Billboard'']] noted Halsey's solo verse as a favorable part of the song, and the song earned her a [[Grammy Award]] nomination for [[Best Pop Duo/Group Performance]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/dance/7453685/chainsmokers-halsey-closer|title=The Chainsmokers & Halsey's New Song 'Closer' Sounds Like an Instant Classic|website=Billboard|access-date=February 27, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.grammy.com/nominees|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120201120225/http://www.grammy.com/nominees|url-status=dead|archive-date=February 1, 2012|title=Nominees And Winners {{!}} GRAMMY.com|date=February 1, 2012|access-date=March 24, 2019}}</ref>\n\n=== 2017\u20132018: ''Hopeless Fountain Kingdom'' ===\nHalsey announced work on her second studio album prior to the release of ''Badlands'', with progress on the record continuing throughout 2016 and 2017.<ref>{{cite av media|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=DeWb_-fEKfI|title=Firefly 2015: Halsey Explains Why She Wants to Leak Her Own Album|date=June 21, 2015|work=YouTube}}</ref> In January 2017, she released the single \"[[Not Afraid Anymore]]\"; it appears on the [[Fifty Shades Darker: Original Motion Picture Soundtrack|soundtrack]] of the film ''[[Fifty Shades Darker (film)|Fifty Shades Darker]]'' (2017).<ref>{{cite web|last1=Romaine|first1=Jenna|title=Listen to Halsey's Mercurial 'Not Afraid Anymore' Off Upcoming 'Fifty Shades Darker' Soundtrack|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/7655123/halsey-not-afraid-anymore-fifty-shades-darker-soundtrack-song-listen|website=Billboard|accessdate=June 12, 2017}}</ref> \"[[Now or Never (Halsey song)|Now or Never]]\" was released on April 4 as the lead single from her second studio album, and because it preceded the release of her second studio album, it was released as an instant grat with the album's pre-order.<ref>{{Citation|title=hopeless fountain kingdom (Deluxe) by Halsey|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/hopeless-fountain-kingdom-deluxe/1221749987|language=en-us|access-date=February 27, 2019}}</ref> The song debuted at number 52 on the US [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]] and later peaked at number 17. It was certified 2x Platinum by the [[Recording Industry Association of America|RIAA]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.riaa.com/gold-platinum/|title=Gold & Platinum|website=RIAA|language=en-US|access-date=December 27, 2018}}</ref> \"Now or Never\" also reached the top 20 of Australia and Malaysia, and sold 500,000 units outside of the US.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ariacharts.com.au/charts/singles-chart|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170610082804/https://www.ariacharts.com.au/charts/singles-chart|url-status=dead|archive-date=June 10, 2017|title=ARIA Australian Top 50 Singles Chart{{!}} Australia's Official Top 50 Songs - ARIA Charts {{!}} ARIA Charts|date=June 10, 2017|access-date=February 28, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.rim.org.my/main/images/stories/RIM/chart/16_i_dm.pdf|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170712133504/http://www.rim.org.my/main/images/stories/RIM/chart/16_i_dm.pdf|url-status=dead|archive-date=July 12, 2017|title=Wayback Machine|date=July 12, 2017|access-date=February 28, 2019}}</ref> Two promotional singles were also made available prior to the release of the album: \"[[Eyes Closed (Halsey song)|Eyes Closed]]\" and \"[[Strangers (Halsey song)|Strangers]]\"'.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2017/music/reviews/halsey-the-weeknd-eyes-closed-1202409804/|title=Review: Halsey Changes Gears With Weeknd Collaboration 'Eyes Closed'|last1=Aswad|first1=Jem|date=May 4, 2017|website=Variety|accessdate=May 8, 2017}}</ref>\n\nHalsey released her second studio album, ''[[Hopeless Fountain Kingdom]]'', on June 2.<ref>{{cite web |last=Stutz |first=Colin |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/7717159/halsey-new-album-title-hopeless-fountain-kingdom-date |title=Halsey Announces New Album Title, Release Month |work=Billboard |date=March 7, 2017 |accessdate=March 8, 2017}}</ref> The album consisted of more \"radio friendly\" songs in comparison to her previous work, which she attributed to her desire to prove she was \"more than capable\" of creating \"radio-ready\" music.<ref name=\"background\">{{cite web|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/features/halsey-on-sci-fi-breakup-album-following-up-closer-w473305|title=Halsey Talks Sci-Fi Breakup Album, Following Up Megahit 'Closer'|work=Rolling Stone|date=March 27, 2017|accessdate=April 1, 2017}}</ref> Much like her debut album, ''Hopeless Fountain Kingdom'' is a concept album that revolves around a pair of lovers in a tale based on [[Romeo and Juliet]]; the project was inspired by her breakup with Lido.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://genius.com/a/how-halsey-flipped-romeo-juliet-on-its-head-with-her-new-album-hopeless-fountain-kingdom|title=How Halsey flipped 'Romeo and Juliet' on its head with her new album 'Hopeless Fountain Kingdom'|publisher=Genius.com}}</ref> The album also focuses on Halsey's bisexuality and on bisexual characters.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://genius.com/Halsey-bad-at-love-lyrics|title=Halsey \u2013 Bad at Love|author=|date=|publisher=|accessdate=January 30, 2019|via=genius.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.popmatters.com/halsey-hopeless-fountain-kingdom-2495389192.html|title=Halsey: Hopeless Fountain Kingdom|author=|date=June 7, 2017|website=PopMatters|accessdate=January 30, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite tweet|user=halsey|number=1009529841131982848|date=June 20, 2018|author=Halsey|title=It literally IS a bisexual story}}</ref> ''Hopeless Fountain Kingdom'' debuted atop the [[Billboard 200|''Billboard'' 200]] and the [[Canadian Albums Chart]]. First week sales in the US were of 106,000 equivalent album units, with 76,000 being pure album sales. Similar to her debut album, ''Hopeless Fountain Kingdom'' was certified Platinum by the RIAA.<ref name=\"Billboard debut\">{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/7825776/halsey-hopeless-fountain-kingdom-no-1-album-billboard-200-chart|title=Halsey Earns First No. 1 Album on Billboard 200 Chart With 'Hopeless Fountain Kingdom'|first=Keith|last=Caulfield|work=Billboard|date=June 11, 2017|accessdate=June 12, 2017}}</ref> Due to the album reaching number one, Halsey became the first woman to achieve a number one album in the US in 2017.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://observer.com/2017/06/halsey-buys-house-beachwood-canyon-los-angeles/|title=Halsey Has the Perfect New House to Celebrate Her Album In|date=June 15, 2017|website=Observer|language=en|access-date=February 28, 2019}}</ref> To promote the album, Halsey embarked on the [[Hopeless Fountain Kingdom World Tour]], which began on September 29, 2017, her twenty-third birthday.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.altpress.com/news/entry/halsey_announces_hopeless_fountain_kingdom_tour_dates|title=Halsey announces 'hopeless fountain kingdom' tour dates|website=Alternative Press}}</ref> Halsey also performed surprise DJ sets at Emo Nite in Los Angeles in 2017.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://earmilk.com/2017/10/17/living-it-up-from-emo-nite-to-emo-nite-day-interview/|title=Living It Up From Emo Nite to Emo Nite Day|publisher=Ear Milk}}</ref>\n[[File:Halsey, 2018.png|thumb|right|upright|Halsey performing during her [[Hopeless Fountain Kingdom Tour]] in July 2018]]\n\nThe second single from ''Hopeless Fountain Kingdom'', \"[[Bad at Love]]\", was released on August 22. The song peaked at number five in the US, which made it her highest peak as a lead artist at the time.<ref name=\":5\">{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/halsey/chart-history/hot-100/song/1029084|title=Halsey Bad At Love Chart History|website=Billboard.com|accessdate=January 27, 2018}}</ref> It was certified 4x Platinum by the RIAA, and sold more than 300,000 records outside the US.<ref name=\"Gold & Platinum\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.riaa.com/gold-platinum/|title=Gold & Platinum|website=RIAA|language=en-US|access-date=February 28, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://musiccanada.com/gold-platinum/|title=Gold/Platinum|website=Music Canada|language=en-US|access-date=February 28, 2019|archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6iYPUE2rD?url=http://musiccanada.com/gold-platinum/|archive-date=June 26, 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.auspop.com.au/2018/2/aria-chart-watch-458/|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180203124043/https://www.auspop.com.au/2018/2/aria-chart-watch-458/|url-status=dead|archive-date=February 3, 2018|title=ARIA CHART WATCH #458 {{!}} auspOp|date=February 3, 2018|access-date=February 28, 2019}}</ref> In December, Halsey's collaboration with then boyfriend [[G-Eazy]] \"[[Him & I]]\" was released, and later peaked at number 14 on the ''Billboard'' Hot 100,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/g-eazy|title=G-Eazy Chart History|author=|date=|website=Billboard|accessdate=January 30, 2019}}</ref> and was certified 2x Platinum by RIAA.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.riaa.com/gold-platinum/|title=Gold & Platinum|author=|date=|website=RIAA|accessdate=January 30, 2019}}</ref> The song also reached the top ten of 13 other countries' charts.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/8240709/g-eazy-halsey-him-and-i-pop-songs-chart|title=G-Eazy & Halsey's 'Him & I' Hits No. 1 on Pop Songs Airplay Chart|website=Billboard|access-date=February 28, 2019}}</ref> In mid 2017 she collaborated with the band [[Thirty Seconds to Mars]] on the song \"Love Is Madness\" for their album ''[[America (Thirty Seconds to Mars album)|America]]''.<ref>{{cite web |title=America by Thirty Seconds to Mars |url=https://www.qobuz.com/album/america-thirty-seconds-to-mars/m9i97qmnj31ia |publisher=Qobuz |accessdate=June 12, 2018}}</ref>\n\nOn January 13, 2018, Halsey was a featured as a musical guest on ''[[Saturday Night Live]]'' and performed \"Bad at Love\" and \"Him & I\" with G-Eazy.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/8094154/halsey-snl-performance-five-things-we-want-to-see|title=5 Things We Want to See From Halsey's 'SNL' Performance|website=Billboard|access-date=April 19, 2019}}</ref> On March 15, Halsey released \"[[Alone (Halsey song)|Alone]]\", along with a new version featuring American rapper [[Big Sean]] and British rapper [[Stefflon Don]]. It was released as the third and final single from ''Hopeless Fountain Kingdom'', and in April she released its music video.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/8248110/halsey-alone-remix-featuring-big-sean-stefflon-don-listen|title=Halsey's 'Alone' Gets a Fresh Remix Featuring Big Sean & Stefflon Don: Listen|website=Billboard|access-date=January 31, 2019}}</ref> \"Alone\" was certified Platinum by RIAA and reached number one on ''Billboard's'' [[Dance Club Songs|Dance Club]] chart, though only peaked at number 66 on the ''Billboard'' Hot 100.<ref name=\"Gold & Platinum\"/><ref name=\"ReferenceA\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/halsey|title=Halsey Chart History|website=Billboard|access-date=February 28, 2019}}</ref> Halsey sang with [[Khalid (singer)|Khalid]] for [[Benny Blanco]]'s debut single \"[[Eastside (song)|Eastside]]\", which was released on July 12, along with a music video discussing various parts of Halsey's life.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.spin.com/2018/07/benny-blanco-eastside-halsey-khalid-stream/|title=Benny Blanco \u2013 \"Eastside\" (ft. Halsey & Khalid)|date=July 12, 2018|work=Spin|access-date=August 30, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Citation|last=benny blanco|title=benny blanco, Halsey & Khalid \u2013 Eastside (official video)|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=56WBK4ZK_cw|access-date=December 17, 2018}}</ref> The song peaked at number nine on the ''Billboard'' Hot 100 and topped the charts of five other countries.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.uselessdaily.com/world/halsey-trivia-95-facts-about-the-musician-that-has-taken-the-world-by-storm/|title=Halsey is one of the singers and musicians that has made a huge impact in the airplays! Her catchy tunes stuck in your mind! {{!}} Useless Daily: The amazing facts, news & trivia free newsletter!|date=March 25, 2019|website=uselessdaily.com|language=en-US|access-date=March 27, 2019}}</ref> It was certified 2x Platinum in the US, and sold over one million units outside the country.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.riaa.com/gold-platinum/|title=Gold & Platinum|website=RIAA|language=en-US|access-date=April 19, 2019}}</ref> Also this year she appeared in two films: she voiced [[Wonder Woman]] in ''[[Teen Titans Go! To the Movies]]'', and cameoed as herself in ''[[A Star Is Born (2018 film)|A Star Is Born]]'', directed by [[Bradley Cooper]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2018/04/halsey-sony-pictures-movie-deal-life-story-1202376737/|title=Sony Pictures Makes Deal With Halsey For Movie Inspired By Singer's Life|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|first=Mike|last=Fleming Jr|date=April 26, 2018|accessdate=April 26, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |first=Brian |last=Truitt |date=March 12, 2018 |url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/life/movies/2018/03/12/exclusive-halsey-plays-wonder-woman-lil-yachty-green-lantern-teen-titans-go/415282002/|title=Exclusive: Nicolas Cage plays Superman, Halsey is Wonder Woman in 'Teen Titans GO!'|work=[[USA Today]] |access-date=December 4, 2018|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://people.com/music/halsey-has-cameo-lady-gaga-a-star-is-born/|title=Halsey Reveals She Has a Small Cameo in Lady Gaga's A Star Is Born: 'It Was So Humbling'|work=People|access-date=December 4, 2018|language=en}}</ref> Halsey was also a key advisor on the [[The Voice (American TV series)|U.S. version]] of ''[[The Voice (franchise)|The Voice]]'' in its [[The Voice (American season 15)|fifteenth season]].<ref>{{cite magazine | first1=Lily | last1=Milman | url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/television/8469088/the-voice-announces-new-advisors-details | title='The Voice' Announces Halsey, CeeLo Green, Thomas Rhett and Keith Urban as New Advisors | magazine=Billboard | date=August 7, 2018 | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180807231714/https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/television/8469088/the-voice-announces-new-advisors-details | archivedate=August 7, 2018}}</ref>\n\n=== 2018\u2013present: ''Manic'' ===\nOn October 4, Halsey released a single titled \"[[Without Me (Halsey song)|Without Me]]\", her first single through [[Capitol Records]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Halsey teases new single 'Without Me' \u2013 watch|url=https://www.nme.com/news/music/halsey-teaser-without-me-2383681|date=September 26, 2018|work=NME.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite av media|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=0-H7gCrFSgw|title=Halsey \u2013 Without Me (Teaser)|date=September 26, 2018|work=YouTube}}</ref> \"Without Me\" is her \"first solo-record since 2017.\" She stated that this song is also very personal to her.<ref name=\":10\">{{cite magazine|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/halseys-breakup-song-without-me-733023/|title=Hear Halsey's Personal New Breakup Song 'Without Me'|last=Blistein|first=Jon|date=October 4, 2018|magazine=Rolling Stone Magazine|access-date=October 20, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.iheart.com/content/2018-11-29-halsey-explains-why-without-me-is-more-than-just-a-breakup-record/|title=Halsey Explains Why 'Without Me' Is More Than Just A Breakup Record|website=iHeartRadio|language=en|access-date=December 17, 2018}}</ref> On October 29, the official music video for \"Without Me\" was released, featuring a \"G-Eazy lookalike\" following their second breakup.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ZAfAud_M_mg|title=Halsey - Without Me|last=HalseyVEVO|date=|publisher=|accessdate=January 30, 2019|via=YouTube}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://pagesix.com/2018/10/30/halseys-without-me-video-features-a-g-eazy-lookalike/|title=Halsey's 'Without Me' video features a G-Eazy lookalike|first=Jaclyn|last=Hendricks|date=October 30, 2018|website=pagesix.com|accessdate=January 30, 2019}}</ref> This song went on to become Halsey's most successful single as a lead artist to date, becoming her first number-one single on the ''Billboard'' Hot 100. It topped the chart for two non-consecutive weeks and remained in the top five for 22 weeks.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://wixx.com/news/articles/2018/dec/17/ariana-grande-halsey-are-first-two-women-to-score-the-top-two-chart-spots-in-more-than-a-year/|title=Ariana Grande & Halsey are first two women to score the top two chart spots in more than a year|last=Inc|first=Midwest Communications|website=101 WIXX|access-date=December 23, 2018}}</ref> It also reached the top three of the UK, Malaysia, Australia, Canada, New Zealand, and Ireland. The song has been certified 3x Platinum in the US, Platinum in the UK, and 5x Platinum in Australia and Canada.<ref name=\"Without Me Halsey song\">{{Citation|title=Without Me (Halsey song)|date=February 27, 2019|url=https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Without_Me_(Halsey_song)&oldid=885395681|work=Wikipedia|language=en|access-date=February 28, 2019}}</ref> Due to \"Without Me\" reaching number one on the ''Billboard'' Hot 100, Halsey became the eighth woman to achieve multiple number ones on the chart during the [[2010s]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/8492429/halsey-without-me-billboard-hot-100-number-one|title=Halsey's 'Without Me' Tops Billboard Hot 100, Becoming Her First No. 1 as a Lead Artist|website=Billboard|access-date=February 28, 2019}}</ref>\n[[File:Halsey @ Grammy Museum 09 23 2019 (49311490491).jpg|thumb|left|upright|Halsey performing in 2019]]\n\nHalsey released or was featured on various collaborations during the first several months of 2019, including a remix of \"Without Me\" featuring American rapper [[Juice WRLD]] on January 9,<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/halsey-juice-wrld-without-me-remix-776590/|title=Hear Halsey Tap Juice WRLD for Stirring 'Without Me' Remix|work=Rolling Stone|access-date=January 15, 2019}}</ref> the song \"[[11 Minutes (song)|11 Minutes]]\" with [[Yungblud]] and featuring [[Travis Barker]] on February 14<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/rock/8498310/halsey-yungblud-11-minutes-travis-barker|title=Yungblud & Halsey Release New Song '11 Minutes' With Travis Barker|website=Billboard|access-date=March 6, 2019}}</ref> and accompanying music video on February 22,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nme.com/news/music/yungblud-halsey-travis-barker-11-minutes-single-2447747|title=Watch Yungblud and Halsey team up with Travis Barker in '11 Minutes' video|last=Moore|first=Sam|date=February 22, 2019|website=NME|language=en-US|access-date=March 6, 2019}}</ref> and the song \"[[Boy with Luv]]\" by [[BTS (band)|BTS]] on April 12, the music video for which became [[List of most-viewed online videos in the first 24 hours|the most\u2013viewed music video within the first 24 hours]] on [[YouTube]] with 74.6 million views.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Spangler |first1=Todd |title=Korea's BTS Shatters YouTube Record for Views in 24 Hours With 'Boy With Luv' Featuring Halsey |url=https://variety.com/2019/digital/news/bts-youtube-record-boy-with-luv-halsey-1203188877/ |accessdate=April 14, 2019 |work=Variety |date=April 13, 2019 |language=en}}</ref> On April 19, she and 29 other musical acts were featured on the [[Lil Dicky]] song \"[[Earth (Lil Dicky song)|Earth]],\" a [[charity single]] about [[climate change]] awareness.<ref name=\":21\">{{Cite web|url=https://consequenceofsound.net/2019/04/lil-dicky-earth-video-song-new-release/|title=Lil Dicky reveals epic \"Earth\" video featuring Justin Bieber, Ariana Grande, Leonardo DiCaprio, more: Watch|date=April 19, 2019|website=Consequence of Sound|language=en-US|access-date=April 22, 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn February 9, Halsey appeared on ''[[Saturday Night Live]]'' as the host and musical guest.<ref name=\"Vulture SNL\">{{cite web |last1=Squires |first1=Bethy |title=Halsey Is Hosting SNL in February |url=https://www.vulture.com/2019/01/halsey-is-hosting-saturday-night-live-february-9.html |website=vulture.com |accessdate=January 28, 2019}}</ref> Her performance was praised, with ratings for the show rising and a younger audience watching.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/02/saturday-night-live-ratings-host-musical-guest-halsey-1202553831/|title='Saturday Night Live' Ratings Rise With Host & Musical Guest Halsey|last=Andreeva|first=Nellie|last2=Andreeva|first2=Nellie|date=February 10, 2019|website=Deadline|language=en|access-date=February 11, 2019}}</ref> In March, Halsey announced that her third studio album would be released in 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.altpress.com/news/halsey-album-confirmation-new/|title=Halsey reveals next album will be released this year|date=March 26, 2019|website=Alternative Press|language=en-US|access-date=March 26, 2019}}</ref> The album is titled ''[[Manic (album)|Manic]]'', and was released in January 2020.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/8529849/halsey-manic-album-title |title=Halsey Announces 'Manic' Album Title, Begins Painting on Mysterious Live Stream |work=Billboard |date=September 12, 2019 |accessdate=September 12, 2019 |author=Aniftos, Rania}}</ref> On May 17, Halsey released the single \"[[Nightmare (Halsey song)|Nightmare]]\", which debuted in the top fifteen of the US.<ref name=\"Twitter\">{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/halsey/status/1126680745387462656|title=new single. NIGHTMARE. may 17th|via=[[Twitter]]|date=May 9, 2019|accessdate=May 19, 2019}}</ref> On September 13, 2019, she released the single \"[[Graveyard (Halsey song)|Graveyard]]\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.altpress.com/news/halsey-graveyard-announcement/|title=Halsey Announces New Track \"Grave Yard\", Artwork Sparks Fan Album Theories|work=[[AltPress]]|last=Shoemaker|first=Whitney|date=September 3, 2019|accessdate=September 10, 2019}}</ref> On September 23, 2019, Halsey announced her upcoming [[concert tour]], named [[Manic World Tour]], in support of her third studio album. The singer will play 19 shows during the first leg, scheduled to take place in Europe between February and March 2020.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nme.com/news/music/halsey-announces-2020-uk-ireland-manic-arena-tour-2550475|author=Andrew Trendell|date=September 23, 2019|accessdate=September 23, 2019|work=[[NME]]|title=Halsey announces 2020 UK and Ireland 'Manic' arena tour}}</ref> She released a promotional single, \"[[Clementine (Halsey song)|Clementine]]\", on her birthday, September 29, 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hotnewhiphop.com/halsey-releases-third-single-clementine-from-upcoming-album-new-song.1984680.html|title=Halsey Releases Third Single, \"Clementine\", From Upcoming Album|website=Hot New Hip Hop|first=Noah|last=C|date=September 29, 2019|accessdate=September 29, 2019}}</ref>  On January 25, 2020 she again appeared on ''Saturday Night Live'' where she performed two songs from her new album Manic, \"You Should be Sad\" and \"Finally//Beautiful Stranger\" as well as appeared in a few sketches.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.complex.com/music/2020/01/halsey-saturday-night-live|title=Watch Halsey Perform 'You Should Be Sad' and \u2018Finally // Beautiful Stranger' on 'Saturday Night Live'|website=Complex}}</ref>\n\nIn December 2019, she appeared on the [[Bring Me the Horizon]] EP ''[[Music to Listen To\u2026]]''. BMTH singer [[Oli Sykes]] later teased additional collaborations;<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://metalinjection.net/upcoming-releases/oli-sykes-confirms-bring-me-the-horizon-halsey-are-teaming-up-for-new-music|title=Oli Sykes Confirms BRING ME THE HORIZON & HALSEY Are Teaming Up For New Music|date=July 29, 2019|website=Metal Injection}}</ref> one of them was revealed a month later to be the Oli Sykes and [[Jordan Fish]]-produced<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://metalinjection.net/av/new-music/heres-that-halsey-song-that-bring-me-the-horizon-co-wrote-for-the-harley-quinn-movie|title=Here's That HALSEY Song That BRING ME THE HORIZON Co-Wrote For The Harley Quinn Movie|date=February 10, 2020|website=Metal Injection}}</ref> song \"Experiment on Me\" to [[Birds of Prey: The Album|the soundtrack]] of the superhero film ''[[Birds of Prey (2020 film)|Birds of Prey]]'', which was released on February 7, 2020.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://wild949.iheart.com/content/2020-01-09-birds-of-prey-soundtrack-includes-halsey-normani-saweetie-more/|title=Birds Of Prey Soundtrack Includes Halsey, Normani, Saweetie & More|publisher=[[iHeartMedia]]|date=January 9, 2020|accessdate=January 9, 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Artistry ==\n\n=== Influences ===\nAs Halsey grew up, her mother listened to [[The Cure]], [[Alanis Morissette]], and [[Nirvana (band)|Nirvana]], while her father listened to [[The Notorious B.I.G.]], [[Slick Rick]], [[Bone Thugs-n-Harmony]], and [[Tupac Shakur|2Pac]]. She said their music taste has been a great influence on her.<ref name=\"dscvr\" /> Halsey called [[Panic! at the Disco]] the \"band that changed [her] fucking life\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nylon.com/articles/halsey-nylon-june-july-cover/page-4|title=Halsey Is Our June/July Cover Star|last=Butterworth|first=Lisa|website=Nylon|accessdate=June 23, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160617120335/http://www.nylon.com/articles/halsey-nylon-june-july-cover/page-4|archive-date=June 17, 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref> and credits [[Lady Gaga]] for giving her the strength to be herself.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/7549028/halsey-lady-gaga-twitter-love|title=Watch Halsey Geek Out to Lady Gaga Tweeting Her|last=Redfearn|first=Dominique|date=October 18, 2016|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|accessdate=October 25, 2016}}</ref> Halsey mentioned a [[Long Island]] [[Rock music|rock]] band, [[Brand New (band)|Brand New]], as both an influence and a favorite of hers, once changing her biography on [[Instagram]] to \"[[The Devil and God Are Raging Inside Me|the devil and God are raging inside me]]\", a reference to their third album.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/iamhalsey/|title=halsey (@iamhalsey) \u2022 Instagram photos and videos|date=September 29, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160929231211/https://www.instagram.com/iamhalsey/|archive-date=September 29, 2016|url-status=dead|access-date=March 8, 2017}}</ref> Halsey cited [[Taylor Swift]] as a huge reason why she always insisted on writing her own music.<ref>{{cite tweet |user=halsey |number=1145435250295635968|date=July 1, 2019 |title=\ud83e\udd8b @taylorswift13}}</ref> Her other influences include [[Marilyn Manson]], [[Beck]],<ref name=mm>{{cite web |url=https://www.refinery29.com/en-us/2019/02/224373/halsey-tattoo-marilyn-manson|title=Halsey Just Got A Huge Marilyn Manson Tattoo \u2014 & Fans Are Divided|author=Stalder, Erika|work=[[Refinery29]] |date=February 13, 2019 |accessdate=August 22, 2019}}</ref> [[Kanye West]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.redeyechicago.com/music/redeye-halsey-interview-20150320-story.html|title=Honesty is the best policy for rising star Halsey|last=Pais|first=Matt|date=March 24, 2015|work=[[RedEye]]|accessdate=February 11, 2016}}</ref> [[The Weeknd]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.oystermag.com/halsey-on-satire-sexuality-and-finding-solace-in-music|title=Halsey On Satire, Sexuality And Finding Solace In Music|last=Kazemi|first=Alex|date=August 27, 2015|work=[[Oyster (magazine)|Oyster]]|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160920114130/http://www.oystermag.com/halsey-on-satire-sexuality-and-finding-solace-in-music|archivedate=September 20, 2016|url-status=dead|accessdate=August 5, 2016}}</ref> [[Amy Winehouse]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.teenvogue.com/story/sound-scout-halsey-interview|title=Sound Scout: Meet Halsey, Songstress Who's Making Waves With Her Feminist Pop Mystique|last=Thurmond|first=Alexandra|date=April 11, 2015|work=[[Teen Vogue]]|accessdate=January 11, 2017}}</ref> and [[Bright Eyes (band)|Bright Eyes]].<ref name=\"Noisey\" />\n\nHalsey has said \"There's plenty of musicians that I love and respect, but I think that I'm the most inspired by cinema.\"<ref name=\"mtv uk\">{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.co.uk/halsey/news/halsey-reveals-the-unconventional-inspiration-behind-badlands-could-there-be-a-screenplay-about-it-to-come|title=Halsey Reveals The Unconventional Inspiration Behind 'Badlands' & Could There Be A Screenplay About It To Come?|author-last=Downing|author-first=Megan|date=January 19, 2016|website=[[MTV UK]]|accessdate=July 5, 2016}}</ref> Filmmakers who have influenced her include [[Quentin Tarantino]], [[Harmony Korine]], and [[Larry Clark]].<ref name=\"mtv uk\" />\n\n=== Music style and themes ===\nHalsey is noted for her distinctive \"indie\" style of singing,<ref name=\":0\">{{cite web|url=http://theodysseyonline.com/ksu/reasons-halsey-favorite-artist/180684|title=Reasons Why Halsey Needs to be Your Favorite Artist|author=|date=October 6, 2015|website=The Odyssey Online|accessdate=January 30, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\":3\">{{cite web|url=http://abcnewsradioonline.com/music-news/2018/7/27/halsey-says-using-her-weird-voice-to-play-wonder-woman-in-te.html|title=Halsey says using her \"weird voice\" to play Wonder Woman in \"Teen Titans Go! to the Movies\" is \"her calling\" - Music News - ABC News Radio|author=|date=|website=abcnewsradioonline.com|accessdate=January 30, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\":16\">{{Cite web|url=https://ohnotheydidnt.livejournal.com/109731388.html|title=Bananis and Avocadis : 5 Singers With Indie-Style Singing (ONTD Original)|website=ohnotheydidnt.livejournal.com|language=en|access-date=December 24, 2018}}</ref> which has garnered controversial feedback.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.complex.com/music/2018/10/schoolboy-q-tyga-halsey-mean-tweets-kimmel|title=Schoolboy Q, Tyga, and Halsey Read Some Mean Tweets on 'Kimmel'|website=Complex|language=en|access-date=December 23, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/2743531/is-indie-girl-voice-just-the-latest-version-of-emo-boy-voice/|title=Is 'Indie Girl Voice' Just The Latest Version of 'Emo Boy Voice'?|last=Beauchemin|first=Molly|website=MTV News|language=en|access-date=February 28, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/6889496/halsey-young-performs-blink-182-mall|title=Watch Halsey Perform Blink-182 in a Shopping Mall -- Before She Was Halsey|website=Billboard|access-date=February 28, 2019}}</ref> She sings with an \"accent\" different from her speaking voice.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://vampmusicnashville.wordpress.com/2016/02/04/the-indie-pop-voice-phenomenon-part-1-where-did-it-come-from/|title=The Indie Pop Voice Phenomenon, Part 1: Where Did It Come From?|last=kellyhoppinjams|date=February 4, 2016|website=(voicing all my passions)|language=en|access-date=January 31, 2019}}</ref> She is a [[Pop music|pop]],<ref name=\"USA Today Genres\">{{cite news|first=Maeve|last=Mcdermott |url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/life/entertainthis/2017/06/01/halsey-hopeless-fountain-kingdom-review-future-of-pop-music/102356426/|title=Is Halsey's 'Hopeless Fountain Kingdom' the future of pop music?|newspaper=[[USA Today]]|accessdate=June 20, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"AllMusic Genres\">{{cite web|first=Timothy|last=Monger |url=https://www.allmusic.com/artist/halsey-mn0003010517/discography|title=Halsey Bio|website=[[AllMusic]]|accessdate=June 20, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite magazine|title=Halsey's 'Nightmare' May Not Become Her Biggest Single, But It's Her Most Important One|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/8512254/halsey-nightmare-importance-video-analysis|magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|first=Jason|last=Lipshutz|date=May 20, 2019|accessdate=August 13, 2019}}</ref> [[electropop]],<ref name=\"AllMusic Genres\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.flare.com/celebrity/electro-pop-singer-halsey-girls-are-angry-and-they-should-be/|title=Halsey Talks Social Media and Selling Out a Tour |website=Flare|language=en-US|accessdate=December 15, 2015}}</ref><ref name=\"Billboard Genres\">{{cite web|url=https://billboard.com/articles/news/6671107/halsey-the-weeknd-drugs-badlands-billboard-feature|title=Art-Pop Singer Halsey on Being Bipolar, Bisexual and an 'Inconvenient Woman' {{!}} Billboard|website=Billboard|accessdate=December 15, 2015}}</ref><ref name=\"Photo Gallery\">{{cite web|url=http://www.vanyaland.com/2015/07/02/photo-gallery-rising-alt-pop-singer-halsey-lights-up-td-garden-last-night-in-boston/|title=Photo Gallery: Rising alt-pop singer Halsey lights up TD Garden last night in Boston|website=Vanyaland|accessdate=December 15, 2015}}</ref> [[synth-pop]],<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/7751504/halsey-now-or-never-video|title=Watch Halsey's Graphic New Video for 'Now or Never'|last=Frankel|first=Jillian|date=April 4, 2017|work=Billboard|access-date=June 7, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.altpress.com/news/entry/halsey_teases_new_ghost_music_video|title=Halsey teases new \"Ghost\" music video|date=June 10, 2015|work=Alternative Press|access-date=June 7, 2017|language=en}}</ref> [[art pop]],<ref name=\"Billboard Genres\"/> [[Alternative rock|alternative pop]],<ref name=\"Photo Gallery\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/laurenalvarez/2019/09/29/halsey-celebrates-her-25th-birthday-with-new-clementine-music-video/#2595163955d2|title=Halsey Celebrates Her 25th Birthday With New 'Clementine' Music Video|website=[[Forbes (magazine)|Forbes]]|first=Lauren|last=Alvarez|date=September 29, 2019|accessdate=September 30, 2019}}</ref> [[Contemporary R&B|R&B]]<ref name=\"USA Today Genres\"/> and [[indie pop]] artist.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theodysseyonline.com/who-the-heck-is-halsey|title=Who The Heck Is Halsey|last=Brown|first=Jason|date=September 21, 2015|access-date=March 6, 2019}}</ref>\n''[[The New York Times]]''{{'}} [[Jon Caramanica]] noted, \"Halsey arrived as part of a slew of female pop rebels who emerged in the wake of [[Lorde]]'s early-2010s recalibration of the genre's operating hierarchies.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2017/05/31/arts/music/halsey-hopeless-fountain-kingdom-review.html|title=Halsey's Second Album: Something New, but a Lot Borrowed|last=Caramanica|first=Jon|date=May 31, 2017|work=[[The New York Times]]}}</ref> When speaking of ''Badlands'', [[Billboard (magazine)|''Billboard'']] stated, \"Halsey's larger-than-life vision combines the synthy darkness of Lorde, the neon-pop chutzpah of [[Miley Cyrus]] and the flickering film noir of [[Lana Del Rey]].\"<ref>{{cite web |author=Chris Martins |title=Art-Pop Singer Halsey on Being Bipolar, Bisexual and an 'Inconvenient Woman' |work=Billboard |date=August 21, 2015 |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/6671107/halsey-the-weeknd-drugs-badlands-billboard-feature |access-date=January 13, 2019}}</ref>\n\nHalsey's music focuses on her personal experiences and telling a story.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.voxmagazine.com/music/halsey-s-new-album-almost-tells-the-full-story/article_2323c76c-49a8-11e7-982c-773fd7ab6d1c.html|title=Halsey's new album almost tells the full story|last=Epps|first=Zach Van|website=Vox Magazine|language=en|access-date=April 15, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://theodysseyonline.com/ksu/reasons-halsey-favorite-artist/180684|title=Reasons Why Halsey Needs to be Your Favorite Artist|date=October 6, 2015|website=The Odyssey Online|language=en-us|access-date=April 15, 2019}}</ref> She writes about relationships with other women in her music as a way of solidifying her bisexuality.<ref name=\"advocate.com\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.advocate.com/bisexuality/2018/10/12/halsey-defends-bisexuals-after-claims-shes-not-lgbtq-community|title=Halsey Defends Bisexuals After Claims She's Not in LGBTQ Community|date=October 12, 2018|website=advocate.com|language=en|access-date=March 17, 2019}}</ref>\n\n=== Videos and stage ===\nThe biggest influence on her live performances is [[Adam Lazzara]], the frontman of [[Taking Back Sunday]],<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.fuse.tv/2015/08/halsey-style-guide |title= 10 ways to adopt halsey's style: a guide to being a badass | author-first= Maria | author-last= Sherman | date= August 31, 2015 |website= [[Fuse (TV channel)|fuse]] |accessdate= July 5, 2016}}</ref> as she said, \"One of the most inspiring things I've ever seen is watching [Taking Back Sunday] live and watching Adam use that microphone as a prop and I thought yep, I'm gonna do that.\"<ref name=\"Noisey\">{{cite web|last1=Garland|first1=Emma|title=A First Date with Halsey, the New Queen of the Tumblr Generation|url=http://noisey.vice.com/blog/a-first-date-with-halsey|website=Noisey|publisher=Vice Media|accessdate=April 19, 2016}}</ref>\n\n== Public image ==\n[[File:Halsey MTV Movie &amp; TV Awards.png|thumb|Halsey at the [[2018 MTV Movie & TV Awards]]]]\nIn her early career, Halsey drew criticism for pre-fame [[Tweets (Twitter)|Tweets]] that were posted from 2009\u20132012,<ref name=\":18\" /> and also gained controversy for allegedly calling herself \"tri-bi\" in an interview, due to her being biracial, bipolar, and bisexual; however, she stated the label is a trivializing way to describe her and condemned the label as a misquote.<ref name=\":18\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.livejournal.com/login.bml?returnto=https://ohnotheydidnt.livejournal.com/97680583.html?thread=16859444167&amp;errmsg=notloggedin|title=Log in|website=livejournal.com|language=en-us|access-date=February 28, 2019}}{{Dead link|date=January 2020}}</ref> She became most known for her signature dyed blue hair in her early career.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/photos/7511343/halsey-hair-evolution|title=Halsey's Hair Evolution, From Blue 'Dos to Buzz Cuts|website=Billboard|access-date=February 28, 2019}}</ref> She drew controversy in 2016 after several fan interactions, some involving Halsey kissing underage fans.<ref name=\"Is Halsey Problematic\">{{Cite web|url=https://studybreaks.com/culture/halsey-problematic/|title=Is Halsey Problematic?|date=May 14, 2018|website=Study Breaks|language=en-US|access-date=February 28, 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn June 2017, Halsey received backlash for collaborating with [[Quavo]], an artist who has made homophobic remarks. She stated that she has never spoken to Quavo, and continued to say that she wouldn't put \"a lot of people\" on her songs. She criticized [[Iggy Azalea]] for her \"complete disregard for black culture\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://fuse.tv/2017/06/halsey-apology-iggy-azalea-diss-quavo|title=Halsey Responds to Backlash After Calling Iggy Azalea a 'F-cking Moron'|last=News|website=Fuse|access-date=February 28, 2019}}</ref> She also criticized [[Demi Lovato]] for, in Halsey's view, treating bisexuality as taboo in the song \"[[Cool for the Summer]].\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nme.com/news/halsey-deletes-tweets-criticising-demi-lovato-media-2098940|title=Halsey deletes tweets criticising Demi Lovato and the media|last=Butler|first=Will|date=July 5, 2017|website=NME|language=en-US|access-date=February 28, 2019}}</ref>\n\nHalsey has described herself as an \"in-between role model,\" and an \"inconvenient woman\" due to her music and style.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.elle.com/culture/celebrities/q-and-a/a28577/halsey-music-bipolar/|title=Halsey Opens Up About Being a Reluctant Role Model|last=Harman|first=Justine|date=May 27, 2015|website=ELLE|language=en-US|access-date=February 28, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.popbuzz.com/music/artists/halsey/news/iheartradio-outfit-red-carpet/|title=The internet is roasting Halsey's outfit at the iHeartRadio Music Awards|website=PopBuzz|language=en|access-date=March 18, 2019}}</ref> She stated in 2017 that although she passes as white, she is a black woman and proud of her heritage.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.allure.com/story/halsey-natural-curly-hair|title=Halsey Isn't Here for Trolls Who Criticize Her Naturally Curly Hair|last=Nast|first=Cond\u00e9|website=Allure|language=en|access-date=February 28, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.huffingtonpost.com/entry/halsey-opens-up-about-being-a-white-passing-black-woman_us_599da8f3e4b0d97c4000b33b|title=Halsey Opens Up About Being A 'White-Passing' Black Woman|last=Blay|first=Zeba|date=August 23, 2017|work=Huffington Post|access-date=February 28, 2019|language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bet.com/music/2017/08/17/halsey-black-woman-playboy-magazine-internet-reactions.html?cid=facebook|title=Singer Halsey Says She's a 'Black Woman' And The Internet Has Questions|website=BET.com|access-date=March 17, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nme.com/news/music/halsey-opens-white-guilt-bi-racial-struggles-2125227|title=Halsey opens up about 'white guilt' and her bi-racial struggles|last=Andrew Trendell|date=August 16, 2017|website=NME|language=en-US|access-date=March 17, 2019}}</ref> She has appeared on the cover of magazines such as [[Forbes 30 Under 30]], [[Billboard (magazine)|''Billboard'']], [[Paper (magazine)|Paper]], and [[Playboy]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.buzzfeed.com/morganmurrell/halseys-having-one-of-the-best-years-ever-and-im-proud-af|title=15 Reasons Why Halsey Basically Owned 2017|last=Murrell|first=Morgan|website=BuzzFeed|language=en|access-date=February 28, 2019}}</ref> She has appeared in advertisements for [[Jeep]], [[Beats Electronics]], and [[ModCloth]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://adage.com/creativity/work/halsey-renegade-30s/52893|title=Is This an Ad for Halsey or an Ad for Jeep?|last=Dumenco|first=Simon|website=adage.com|language=en|access-date=March 18, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ispot.tv/ad/dE9c/beats-audio-studio3-wireless-music-the-way-halsey-intended|title=Beats Audio Studio3 Wireless TV Commercial, 'Music The Way Halsey Intended' Featuring Zane Lowe|website=iSpot.tv|language=en|access-date=March 18, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/pride/8501339/halsey-awkwafina-modcloth-campaign-international-womens-day|title=Halsey, Awkwafina & More Star in New ModCloth Campaign For International Women's Day|website=Billboard|access-date=March 18, 2019}}</ref> She has been described a feminist icon.<ref name=\"onmogul.com\">{{Cite web|url=https://onmogul.com/articles/why-halsey-is-music-s-newest-feminist-icon|title=Why Halsey is Music's Newest Feminist Icon|website=Mogul|language=en|access-date=February 28, 2019}}</ref> She has also been called the \"voice of her generation\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/cover-story/6971430/billboard-cover-halsey-on-fans-fame-music-success|title=Billboard Cover: How Halsey Became the Voice of Her Generation Through Tweets, Tumblr and Truth-Telling|website=Billboard|access-date=February 28, 2019}}</ref> Her relationship with [[G-Eazy]] gathered significant media attention due to rumors of drug usage, arrest, cheating, and G-Eazy's feuds with other artists.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.yahoo.com/lifestyle/8-cringey-details-halsey-g-060123175.html|title=8 Cringey Details About Halsey And G-Eazy's Relationship, Including Rumors They Do Drugs Together|website=yahoo.com|language=en-US|access-date=February 28, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nme.com/news/music/halsey-responds-pathetic-machine-gun-kelly-dragged-eminem-g-eazy-2382840|title=Halsey responds to \"pathetic\" Machine Gun Kelly after being dragged into Eminem and G-Eazy feud|last=Reilly|first=Nick|date=September 24, 2018|website=NME|language=en-US|access-date=February 28, 2019}}</ref>\n\nHalsey has long identified as an [[Alternative Music|alternative]] artist, stating that she can do pop collaborations without being considered a pop artist, similar to [[Kendrick Lamar]]. She states that she is only classified as pop because she is a woman.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/7800866/halsey-interview-video-lauren-jauregui-collaboration|title=Halsey Talks Lauren Jauregui Collaboration, Compares Kendrick Lamar to Lady Gaga in New Interview|website=Billboard|access-date=February 28, 2019}}</ref> Some of her music is still labeled pop while some is considered alternative.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.baeblemusic.com/musicblog/5-24-2017/halseys-genre-identity-crisis.html|title=Halsey's Genre Identity Crisis|website=Baeble Music|access-date=February 28, 2019}}</ref> In 2019, she called herself \"the anti-popstar\" and stated she doesn't care how people identify her music, as long as it connects to people.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/halsey/status/1083082092068720641|title=Part of being an artist is that I can subscribe to whatever brand of myself I wish. Anti-popstar is more about a mentality I think. It has little to do with genre and more about denying the notion that female pop artists should succumb to the social expectations of the genre!|last=h|date=January 9, 2019|website=@halsey|language=en|access-date=February 28, 2019}}</ref>\n\n== Activism ==\nDuring the [[2016 United States presidential election]], Halsey was an avid supporter of [[Bernie Sanders]] and urged her fans to vote for him.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/6897171/halsey-bernie-sanders-love-election-2016|title=Halsey on 2016 Presidential Election: 'I Love Bernie Sanders So Much'|date=March 1, 2016|website=Billboard|access-date=March 26, 2019}}</ref> In July 2016, she and 26 other artists were featured on the [[charity single]] \"[[Hands (2016 song)|Hands]]\", which was a tribute for the victims of the [[Pulse nightclub attack|Pulse nightclub shooting]].<ref name=\":19\" /><ref name=\":20\" />\n\nAs a result of her own attempted suicide at age 17,<ref name=\"Morris2016\" /><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.elle.com/culture/celebrities/q-and-a/a28577/halsey-music-bipolar/|title=Halsey Opens Up About Being a Reluctant Role Model|last=Hartman|first=Justine|date=May 27, 2015|work=Elle|accessdate=August 25, 2015}}</ref> Halsey participated in the mental health and [[suicide prevention]] awareness campaign called \"I'm Listening\", which was hosted by radio network [[Entercom]] and broadcast live on September 10, 2017.<ref name=\":6\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/7950167/halsey-logic-passion-pit-michael-angelakos-mental-health-awareness-suicide-prevention-campaign|title=Halsey, Logic, Michael Angelakos & More To Participate in Mental Health Awareness & Suicide Prevention Campaign 'I'm Listening'|last=Havens|first=Lyndsey|date=September 5, 2015|work=Billboard|access-date=September 21, 2017}}</ref>\n\nHalsey is a feminist.<ref name=\"onmogul.com\"/> After the [[2017 Women's March]], Halsey sent out a tweet that promised to donate one dollar to [[Planned Parenthood]] for every retweet it received.<ref name=\":14\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.nydailynews.com/entertainment/halsey-pledges-donate-100-000-planned-parenthood-article-1.2954946|title=Halsey pledges to donate $100,000 to Planned Parenthood after social media campaign |last=Feldman |first=Kate |work=New York Daily News |access-date=November 27, 2018|language=en-US}}</ref> She ended up donating $100,000 to Planned Parenthood.<ref name=\":14\" /> Halsey delivered a speech to more than 200,000 protesters at the [[2018 Women's March]].<ref name=\":02\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/culture/news/womens-march-scarlett-johansson-viola-davis-halsey-speeches-w515693|title=See Rousing Women's March Speeches from Halsey, Viola Davis and More|work=Rolling Stone|access-date=February 19, 2018}}</ref><ref name=\":2\">{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2018/01/20/us/womens-march.html|title=Women's March 2018: Protestors Take to the Streets for the Second Straight Year|last=|first=|date=January 20, 2018|website=The New York Times|access-date=}}</ref>  Instead of a traditional speech, Halsey performed a five-minute poem titled \"A Story Like Mine\", in which she told personal stories of sexual assault and violence throughout her life.<ref name=\":02\" /> Her personal narrative included accompanying her best friend to Planned Parenthood after she had been raped, her personal account of sexual assault by neighbors and boyfriends, and women sexually assaulted by Olympic doctor [[Larry Nassar]].<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite book|url=https://archive.org/details/celebritypowerfa0000mars|url-access=registration|quote=celebrity empowerment.|title=Celebrity and Power: Fame in Contemporary Culture|last=Marshall|first=P.&nbsp;David|date=1997|publisher=U. of Minnesota Press|isbn=9780816627257|language=en}}</ref> She completed her speech by requesting all\u2014\"Black, Asian, poor, wealthy, trans, cis, Muslim, Christian\"\u2014sexual assault victims to listen and support each other.<ref name=\":1\" /> A.&nbsp;J.&nbsp;Willingham of ''[[CNN]]'' opined in a headline that \"Halsey's Women's March speech moved people around the world.\"<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.cnn.com/2018/01/22/us/halsey-womens-march-poem-speech-trnd/index.html|title=Halsey's Women's March speech moved people around the world|first=AJ |last=Willingham|work=CNN|access-date=March 21, 2018}}</ref> In March 2018, Halsey protested alongside numerous other celebrities at [[March for Our Lives]] in [[Washington, D.C.]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.refinery29.com/en-us/2018/03/194617/kim-kardashian-miley-cyrus-natalie-portman-march-for-our-lives-celebrities|title=These Celebrities Showed Up To Support March For Our Lives|last=Harris|first=Marquita|website=refinery29.com|language=en|access-date=April 15, 2019}}</ref> In May 2018 Halsey attacked [[Ivanka Trump]] over [[Twitter]], complaining that she was too relaxed while her father, president [[Donald Trump]], hurt immigrant children.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/8458053/halsey-calls-out-ivanka-trump-photo-with-son-1500-missing-immigrant-children|title=Halsey Calls Out Ivanka Trump Over Photo with Son Amid Anger About Government 'Missing' 1,500 Immigrant Children|website=Billboard|access-date=February 28, 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn November 2018 Halsey performed at the [[Victoria's Secret Fashion Show 2018|Victoria's Secret Fashion Show]], along numerous other artists,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.eonline.com/news/985166/halsey-channels-her-inner-angel-at-the-2018-victoria-s-secret-fashion-show|title=Halsey Channels Her Inner Angel at the Victoria's Secret Fashion Show|date=November 8, 2018|website=E! Online|language=en-US|access-date=December 23, 2018}}</ref> but in December she called out the company for its lack of inclusion of [[transgender]] models in its various shows, stating \"as a member of the LGBT+ community, I have no tolerance for a lack of inclusivity. Especially not motivated by stereotype.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.aol.com/article/entertainment/2018/12/03/halsey-criticizes-victorias-secret-over-transgender-comments/23607215/|title=Halsey called out Victoria's Secret over transgender comments: 'I have no tolerance for' that|last=Staff|first=A. O. L.|website=AOL.com|language=en|access-date=December 23, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/newsbeat-46423671|title=Halsey criticises Victoria's Secret|date=December 3, 2018|work=BBC News|access-date=December 23, 2018|language=en-GB}}</ref> Later that month, she performed her hit song \"[[Without Me (Halsey song)|Without Me]]\" on [[The Voice (U.S. TV series)|''The Voice'']] and received backlash for \"sensually\" dancing with backup dancer [[Jade Chynoweth]]. Many called the backlash [[Homophobia|homophobic]] and Halsey defended her performance.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://nylon.com/halsey-the-voice-performance|title=Halsey Responds To 'Homophobic' Backlash Of Her Recent Performance|date=December 21, 2018|website=Nylon|language=en|access-date=December 23, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/life/tv/2018/12/20/voice-finale-halsey-without-me-jade-chynoweth/2373402002/|title=Halsey defends 'Voice' performance with dancer Jade Chynoweth, slams 'homophobic viewers'|website=USA Today |language=en|access-date=December 24, 2018}}</ref> In a January 2019 interview with [[Glamour (magazine)|''Glamour'']], she advocated for a stronger presence of women in music.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.glamour.com/story/halsey-cover-interview|title=Halsey Is Just 'Not Having It'|last=Nast|first=Cond\u00e9|website=Glamour|language=en|access-date=February 28, 2019}}</ref> In April 2019, she and 29 other musical acts were featured on the [[charity single]] \"[[Earth (Lil Dicky song)|Earth]]\", which raises [[climate change]] awareness.<ref name=\":21\" />\n\n== Personal life ==\n\n=== Relationships ===\nHalsey is openly [[bisexuality|bisexual]].<ref name=\"advocate.com\"/> From 2015 to 2016, Halsey dated Norwegian producer [[Lido (musician)|Lido]], who helped produce ''Badlands'' and inspired ''Hopeless Fountain Kingdom.''<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.capitalfm.com/artists/halsey/dating-relationship-history-boyfriends/|title=Halsey's Complete Dating History: All Her Ex-Boyfriends From G Eazy To Machine Gun Kelly & More|website=Capital|language=en|access-date=March 24, 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn 2017, she began dating American rapper [[G-Eazy]]. They met at a party in 2017 and although they pursued different music, they found common ground for their collaboration \"[[Him & I]]\", which discussed their love and lifestyle.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bustle.com/p/how-did-halsey-g-eazy-first-meet-the-couple-might-have-met-in-a-totally-normal-way-8007308|title=Halsey & G-Eazy May Have Met In A Completely Normal Way|last=Czachor|first=Emily Mae|website=Bustle|language=en|access-date=March 24, 2019}}</ref> The couple broke up in July 2018; their relationship was off and on again until September of that year when the relationship was officially over.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.eonline.com/news/979806/halsey-and-g-eazy-break-up-again|title=Halsey and G-Eazy Break Up Again|date= October 23, 2018|website=E! Online|language=en-US|access-date=March 24, 2019}}</ref> Halsey confirmed in a 2019 interview with [[Glamour (magazine)|''Glamour'']] that her October 2018 single \"[[Without Me (Halsey song)|Without Me]]\" is partially about their relationship.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/8495577/halsey-interview-without-me-g-eazy-glamour-cover-story|title=Halsey Opens Up About 'Without Me' & G-Eazy Split in 'Glamour'|website=Billboard|access-date=March 24, 2019}}</ref>\n\nShe began dating English alternative rock musician [[Yungblud]] in November 2018.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/B0yl9kkJvRL/|title=halsey on Instagram: \"darling dom. everyone who has met you in this life, for any amount of time at all, will be changed forever because of it. for some, in\u2026\"|last=halsey|date=|website=Instagram|language=en|access-date=August 7, 2019}}</ref> They both met at a bar in Los Angeles which remained a secret,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.iheart.com/featured/jojo-wright/content/2019-03-08-icymi-jojo-talks-with-halsey-and-yungblud/|title=ICYMI: JoJo Talks With Halsey and YUNGBLUD {{!}} JoJo Wright {{!}} iHeartRadio|last=Wright|first=JoJo|date=March 9, 2019|website=iHeart Radio|access-date=August 9, 2019}}</ref> they discussed different topics including music, and ended up collaborating on \"[[11 Minutes (Yungblud song)|11 Minutes]]\",<ref>{{Citation|last=BUILD Series LDN|title=YUNGBLUD Speaks With Us About His New Single '11 Minutes'|volume=|pages=|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_0-Ziy059NU&t=490|date=March 27, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Citation|last=Sang|first=Zach|title=YUNGBLUD Talks 11 Minutes, Working with Halsey and Travis Barker & New Album|date=March 6, 2019|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=6-ziyeAOzN4|volume=|pages=|language=en|access-date=August 9, 2019}}</ref> and were rumored to be in a romantic relationship. Halsey first confirmed their relationship in an interview with [[Capital (radio network)|Capital FM]] in March and celebrated his birthday in August.<ref>{{Citation|last=|first=|title=Halsey Fangirls Over Her Collaboration With BTS \ud83d\udc95 {{!}} FULL INTERVIEW {{!}} Capital|date=April 29, 2019|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_h_8-PCxMb8|volume=|pages=|language=en|access-date=August 9, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/halsey/status/1158454421329608705|title=happy birthday squish @yungblud|last=h|date=August 5, 2019|website=@halsey|language=en|access-date=August 6, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.lifeandstylemag.com/posts/halsey-and-boyfriend-yungblud-pack-on-the-pda-see-pics/|title=Halsey and Rocker Boyfriend Yungblud Pack On the PDA During Cutesy Coffee Date|last=|first=|date=March 1, 2019|website=Life & Style|language=en-US|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190408013019/https://www.lifeandstylemag.com/posts/halsey-and-boyfriend-yungblud-pack-on-the-pda-see-pics/|archive-date=April 8, 2019|url-status=|access-date=April 8, 2019}}</ref> In September of that year, they ended their relationship.<ref>https://people.com/music/halsey-addresses-yungblud-split/</ref>\n\nHalsey is currently in a relationship with actor [[Evan Peters]] as of October 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.usmagazine.com/celebrity-news/news/halsey-and-evan-peters-are-dating/|title=Halsey and Evan Peters Are Dating After Romances With Yungblud and Emma Roberts|date=September 28, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://kissfmseattle.iheart.com/content/2019-10-30-halsey-was-legit-scared-into-confirming-her-relationship-with-evan-peters/|title=Halsey Was Legit Scared Into Confirming Her Relationship With Evan Peters|website=106.1 KISS FM Seattle}}</ref>\n\n=== Personal health ===\nSince the beginning of her career, Halsey has been open about her personal health; in 2015, speaking of her career, she stated \"I'm just this fucked-up stoner kid who made it\".<ref name=\"Morris2016\" />\n\nHalsey has [[bipolar disorder]]. She was diagnosed with this mental disorder at the age of 17, and said that her mother also has it.<ref name=\":11\">{{Cite news |first=Justine |last=Harman |url=https://www.elle.com/culture/celebrities/q-and-a/a28577/halsey-music-bipolar/|title=Halsey Opens Up About Being a Reluctant Role Model|date=May 27, 2015|work=[[Elle (magazine)|Elle]]|access-date=November 26, 2018|language=en-US}}</ref> At that age, Halsey attempted suicide, which is what led to her diagnosis and a 17-day admission to a psychiatric hospital.<ref name=\":12\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.teenvogue.com/story/halsey-opens-up-about-her-endometriosis-surgery|title=Halsey Opened Up About Undergoing Multiple Surgeries and Her Endometriosis|last=McNamara|first=Brittney|work=Teen Vogue|access-date=November 26, 2018|language=en}}</ref><ref name=\"Morris2016\" /> It was not long after her suicide attempt that Halsey began having success in the music industry. She said that singing and performing has helped her manage the symptoms she experiences from having bipolar disorder.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.refinery29.com/en-us/2018/07/204397/halsey-bipolar-mental-illness-interview|title=Halsey Opens Up About Juggling Her Career & Bipolar Disorder|last=Fredette|first=Meagan|date=July 15, 2018|work=|access-date=November 26, 2018|language=en}}</ref> Despite the struggles Halsey has faced as a result of this mood disorder, she said that she embraces being bipolar because it makes her \"really empathetic\".<ref name=\":11\" />\n\nHalsey was diagnosed with [[endometriosis]] in 2016 and went public with it on her Twitter account.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://people.com/health/halsey-hiding-endometriosis-pain/|title=Halsey Is Done with Hiding Her Endometriosis Pain: 'I Can't Pretend Anymore'|website=PEOPLE.com|language=en|access-date=March 24, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vogue.com/article/halsey-g-eazy-blossom-ball-endometriosis|title=Halsey Kept Things Real at the 9th Annual Blossom Ball|last=Nast|first=Cond\u00e9|website=Vogue|language=en|access-date=March 24, 2019}}</ref> Halsey accredits a [[miscarriage]] she experienced in 2015 to her endometriosis, originally stating in 2016 that it was due to her hectic touring schedule.<ref name=\":15\">{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/entertainment-arts-43407531|title=Halsey: Singer speaks about tour miscarriage trauma|date=April 27, 2018|publisher=BBC|access-date=April 28, 2018}}</ref><ref name=\":12\" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nydailynews.com/entertainment/music/singer-halsey-reveals-miscarriage-tour-year-article-1.2730056|title=Singer Halsey reveals she had a miscarriage on last year's tour, just hours before performing in concert|last=BITETTE|first=NICOLE|website=nydailynews.com|access-date=March 24, 2019}}</ref> Only hours after Halsey realized she was having a miscarriage, she went on stage to perform during a tour because she did not want to hurt her career by missing a performance.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.self.com/story/halsey-miscarriage-work|title=When You're Having A Miscarriage, But Have To Go To Work Anyway|last=Barnes|first=Zahra|work=[[Self (magazine)|Self]]|access-date=November 27, 2018|language=en}}</ref>  Halsey chronicled her struggles with endometriosis on the talk show ''[[The Doctors (talk show)|The Doctors]]'' in April 2018, where she revealed she was going to freeze her eggs.<ref name=\":15\" />\n\nAlso in 2018, Halsey spoke out about her endometriosis and the pain it causes at the Blossom Ball, which is run by the Endometriosis Foundation of America.<ref name=\":13\">{{Cite news|url=https://people.com/health/halsey-hiding-endometriosis-pain/|title=Halsey Is Done with Hiding Her Endometriosis Pain: 'I Can't Pretend Anymore'|work=People|access-date=November 26, 2018|language=en}}</ref> At the Blossom Ball, she said, \"Sometimes I'm bloated, I'm on an I.V., I'm sick, I'm on medicine, and I'm backstage, terrified that I'm going to bleed through my clothes in the middle of my show.\"<ref name=\":13\" /> She told people who attended this event that she wanted to speak out because the media often portrays her as having perfect physical health despite her struggle with endometriosis.<ref name=\":13\" /> In January 2017, Halsey underwent surgery in an attempt to lessen the pain caused by the disorder.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/7647866/halsey-surgery-endometriosis|title=Halsey Undergoes Surgery to Treat Endometriosis|work=Billboard|access-date=November 27, 2018}}</ref> Halsey has not disclosed what type of surgery she underwent.<ref name=\":12\" />\n\nOn July 29, 2019, Halsey tweeted \"the best gift I ever got in life was Cheerios being gluten free\", which prompted a fan to ask her if she was gluten free, she responded saying that she was gluten intolerant and within less than two minutes of consuming food containing gluten, her stomach swells up to the comparison of looking 6 months pregnant.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/halsey/status/1155843921479495681|title=the best gift I ever got in life was Cheerios being gluten free.|last=h (@halsey)|date=July 29, 2019|website=twitter|language=en|access-date=July 29, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/halsey/status/1155844674600390656|title=one of those....people who will straight up keel over in pain if they have gluten? yes haha.|last=h (@halsey)|date=July 29, 2019|website=twitter|language=en|access-date=July 29, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/halsey/status/1155845318388281345|title=within t-minus 80 seconds of eating it my belly swells up like I'm legitimately 6 months pregnant and I feel like someone tryna carve their way out through my bellybutton haha. it ain't fun.|last=h (@halsey)|date=July 29, 2019|website=twitter|language=en|access-date=July 29, 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn August 14, 2019, Halsey revealed on Twitter that she [[smoking cessation|quit smoking cigarettes]] after 10 years.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://people.com/music/halsey-quit-smoking-after-10-years/|title=Halsey Reveals She Quit Smoking After 10 Years: 'I'm So Happy I Did It'|work=People}}</ref>\n\n=== Tattoos ===\nHalsey has 29 confirmed tattoos, with her most prominent being an [[Horseshoe#Superstition|upside-down horseshoe]] on her right shoulder.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://pagesix.com/2019/02/12/the-meanings-behind-these-celebrity-tattoos/slide-13/|title=The meaning behind these celebrity tattoos|work=Page Six|quote=Halsey told iHeart Radio about her upside-down horseshoe's meaning, saying, \"I got an upside-down horseshoe to signify that I don't need luck. I work really, really hard, and I believe in the stars aligning, but I don't believe that anything happens to anyone based out of sheer luck. I believe people work really hard, and they manifest what they want, and what they need, and what they're hopeful for, and that's what this is -- a reminder.\"}}</ref> She had a tattoo of \"[[Him & I]]\" lyrics for G-Eazy that has since been covered. She has one tattoo on her face.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.teenvogue.com/story/halsey-face-tattoo|title=Halsey Reveals New Face Tattoo on Instagram|work=Teen Vogue|quote=As for the design? Halsey opted for the letter \"Q\" in red ink, accompanied by a small diamond, which resembled the suit of a Queen of Diamonds playing card. \"Headed straight for the castle. @nal.tattoo \ud83d\udc89\ud83d\udc89 thanks for my first (and only hopefully lol) face tattoo \u2666\ufe0f\u2666\ufe0f\u2666\ufe0f\u2666\ufe0f,\" she captioned the shot.}}</ref> She also has a tattoo of Marilyn Manson's face on the side of her torso and a tattoo of lyrics from Beck's song \"[[Loser (Beck song)|Loser]]\" (1993) on her neck.<ref name=mm/>\n\n== Discography ==\n{{Main|Halsey discography}}\n* ''[[Badlands (Halsey album)|Badlands]]'' (2015)\n* ''[[Hopeless Fountain Kingdom]]'' (2017)\n*''[[Manic (album)|Manic]]'' (2020)\n\n== Filmography ==\n===Music videos===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" | Year\n! scope=\"col\" | Song title\n! scope=\"col\" | Role\n! scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n|-\n| 2017\n| \"[[Now or Never (Halsey song)|Now or Never]]\"\n| Co-director\n| Co-directed with Sing J Lee\n|-\n| 2017\n| \"[[Bad at Love]]\"\n| Co-director\n| Co-directed with Sing J Lee\n|-\n| 2018\n| \"[[Sorry (Halsey song)|Sorry]]\"\n| Co-director\n| Co-directed with Sing J Lee\n|-\n| 2018\n| \"[[Alone (Halsey song)|Alone]]\" <small>(featuring [[Big Sean]] and [[Stefflon Don]])</small>\n| Co-director\n| Co-directed with [[Hannah Lux Davis]]\n|-\n| 2018\n| \"[[Strangers (Halsey song)|Strangers]]\" <small>(featuring [[Lauren Jauregui]])</small>\n| Co-director\n| Co-directed with [[Jessie Hill (director)|Jessie Hill]]\n|}\n\n===Film===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\" | 2018\n|''[[Teen Titans Go! To the Movies]]''\n| [[Wonder Woman]]\n| Voice role\n|-\n|''[[A Star Is Born (2018 film)|A Star Is Born]]''\n| Herself\n| [[Cameo appearance]]\n|-\n|}\n\n===Television===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n|2016\n|''[[Roadies (TV series)|Roadies]]''\n| Herself\n| Episodes: \"The Load Out\" and \"Carpet Season\"\n|-\n| 2017\n|''[[American Dad! (season 14)|American Dad!]]''\n| Cindy\n| Voice role, Episode: \"A Nice Night for a Drive\"\n|-\n| rowspan=\"1\" | 2018\u201320\