st= |date= |publisher=[[Hong Kong Film Awards]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161127152217/http://www.hkfaa.com/rules2016_eng.html |archive-date=27 November 2016 |url-status=live|accessdate=1 March 2017 |df= }}</ref>\n#The film's director is a [[Hong Kong residents|Hong Kong resident]] that holds a [[Hong Kong Identity Card]]\n#At least one of the film's production companies are legally registered in [[Hong Kong SAR]]. \n#At least one person involved in the film's production from any six separate award categories who are [[Hong Kong residents|Hong Kong resident]] holding a [[Hong Kong Identity Card]].\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==Bibliography==\n{{refbegin|30em}}\n*{{Cite book|title=Directory of World Cinema: CHINA 2 |last=Bettinson |first=Gary |publisher=Intellect |date=2015 |isbn=978-1-78320-400-7 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=JcVDCgAAQBAJ&pg=PA41&lpg=PA41 |quote= |via= |ref=harv |df= }}\n*{{Cite book|title=The Hong Kong Filmography |last=Charles |first=John |publisher=McFarland |date=2000 |isbn=978-1-4766-0262-2 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=nLnwCQAAQBAJ&pg=PA142 |quote= |via= |ref=harv |df= }}\n*{{Cite book|title=Horror to the Extreme: Changing Boundaries in Asian Cinema |last=Choi |first=Jinhee |publisher=Hong Kong University Press |date=2009 |isbn=978-962-209-973-9 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=ApeLNDLTq10C&pg=PA59&lpg=PA59 |quote= |via= |ref=harv |df= }}\n*{{Cite book|title=Encyclopedia of Contemporary Chinese Culture |last=Davis |first=Edward L. |publisher=Taylor & Francis Ebooks |date=2004 |isbn=978-1-134-54953-5 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=YL4GS9zju10C&pg=PT314&lpg=PT314 |quote= |via= |ref=harv |df= }}\n*{{Cite book|title=Mabel Cheung Yuen-Ting's An Autumn's Tale: A Cultural Janus |last=Ford |first=Stacilee |publisher=Hong Kong University Press |date=2008 |isbn=978-962-209-894-7 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=GEK755BJOY4C&pg=PA49 |quote= |via= |ref=harv |df= }}\n*{{Cite book|title=The C