{"title_page": "21st Hong Kong Film Awards", "text_new": "{{Infobox film awards\n| number           = 21\n| award            = Hong Kong Film Awards\n| image            = File:21st Hong Kong Film Awards Poster.jpeg\n| caption          = \n| date             = 21 April 2002\n| site             = [[Hong Kong Cultural Centre]]\n| host             = [[Eric Tsang]]<br>[[Cecilia Yip]]<br>[[Jacqueline Pang]]<br>[[Cheung Tat-Ming]]\n| producer         = \n| director         = \n| organizer        = \n| best_picture     = \n| most_wins        = \n| most_nominations = \n| network          = \n| duration         = \n| ratings          = \n| last             = 20th\n| next             = 22nd\n}}\nCeremony for the '''21st Hong Kong Film Awards''' was held on 21 April 2002 in the [[Hong Kong Cultural Centre]] and hosted by [[Eric Tsang]], [[Cecilia Yip]], [[Jacqueline Pang]] and [[Cheung Tat-Ming]]. Twenty-three winners in eighteen categories were unveiled. The year's biggest winner was ''[[Shaolin Soccer]]'', winning six awards in total. Its director and leading actor [[Stephen Chow]] clinched Best Director and a long-awaited Best Actor title after being nominated for the award seven times since [[10th Hong Kong Film Awards|1991]]. The 21st Hong Kong Film Awards also saw the establishment of the Best Asian Film category, open to all non-Hong Kong films commercially released in Hong Kong within the previous calendar year. The first winner for this category is the [[Cinema of Japan|Japanese]] [[animation|animated feature]] ''[[Spirited Away]]''.\n\n==Awards==\nWinners are listed first, highlighted in '''boldface''', and indicated with a double dagger ({{double-dagger}}).<ref name=\"HKFA\">{{cite web|title=List of Awardees of The 21st Hong Kong Film Awards|url=http://www.hkfaa.com/winnerlist21.html|publisher=[[Hong Kong Film Awards]]|accessdate=15 March 2017}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"Mtime\">{{cite web|title=The 21st Hong Kong Film Awards (2002)|url=http://award.mtime.com/17/2002/|publisher=Mtime.com Inc|accessdate=15 March 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"Love HK Film\">{{cite web|title=The 21st  Annual Hong Kong Film Awards|url=http://www.lovehkfilm.com/features/hkfa_2001.htm|publisher=Love HK Film|accessdate=15 March 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"IMDB\">{{cite web|title=Hong Kong Film Awards for 2002|url=https://www.imdb.com/event/ev0000329/2002|publisher=[[IMDb]]|accessdate=15 March 2017}}</ref>\n\n{| class=wikitable\n|-\n| valign=\"top\" width=\"50%\"|\n{{Award category|#eedd82|[[Hong Kong Film Award for Best Film|Best Film]]}}\n*'''''[[Shaolin Soccer]]'''''{{double-dagger}}\n**[[Beijing Rocks]]\n**[[July Rhapsody]]\n**[[Love on a Diet]]\n**[[Lan Yu (film)|Lan Yu]]\n| valign=\"top\" width=\"50%\"|\n{{Award category|#eedd82|[[Hong Kong Film Award for Best Director|Best Director]]}}\n*'''''[[Stephen Chow]] \u2014 [[Shaolin Soccer]]'''''{{double-dagger}}\n**[[Ann Hui]] \u2014 ''[[July Rhapsody]]\n**[[Ann Hui]] \u2014 ''[[Visible Secret]]\n**[[Johnnie To]] and [[Wai Ka-Fai]] \u2014 [[Love on a Diet]]\n**[[Stanley Kwan]] \u2014 ''[[Lan Yu (film)|Lan Yu]]\n|-\n| valign=\"top\" width=\"50%\"|\n{{Award category|#eedd82|[[Hong Kong Film Award for Best Screenplay|Best Screenplay]]}}\n*'''''[[Ivy Ho]] \u2014 [[July Rhapsody]]'''''{{double-dagger}}\n**[[Stephen Chow]] \u2014 [[Tsang Kan-Cheung]] \u2014 [[Shaolin Soccer]] \n**[[GC Goo-Bi]] \u2014 [[Merry-Go-Round (2001 film)|Merry-Go-Round]] \n**[[Vincent Kok]] and [[Pang Ho-Cheung]] \u2014 [[You Shoot, I Shoot]] \n**[[Jimmy Ngai]] \u2014 [[Lan Yu (film)|Lan Yu]] \n| valign=\"top\" width=\"50%\"|\n{{Award category|#eedd82|[[Hong Kong Film Award for Best Actor|Best Actor]]}}\n*'''''[[Stephen Chow]] \u2014 [[Shaolin Soccer]]'''''{{double-dagger}}\n**[[Jacky Cheung]] \u2014 [[July Rhapsody]] \n**[[Andy Lau]] \u2014 [[Love on a Diet]] \n**[[Hu Jun]] \u2014 [[Lan Yu (film)|Lan Yu]] \n**[[Liu Ye (actor)|Liu Ye]] \u2014 [[Lan Yu (film)|Lan Yu]] \n|-\n| valign=\"top\" width=\"50%\"|\n{{Award category|#eedd82|[[Hong Kong Film Award for Best Actress|Best Actress]]}}\n*'''''[[Sylvia Chang]] \u2014 [[Forever and Ever (2001 film)|Forever and Ever]]'''''{{double-dagger}}\n**[[Sammi Cheng]] \u2014 [[Fighting for Love (2001 film)|Fighting for Love]] \n**[[Anita Mui]] \u2014 [[July Rhapsody]] \n**[[Sammi Cheng]] \u2014 [[Love on a Diet]] \n**[[Sammi Cheng]] \u2014 [[Wu Yen]] \n| valign=\"top\" width=\"50%\"|\n{{Award category|#eedd82|[[Hong Kong Film Award for Best Supporting Actor|Best Supporting Actor]]}}\n*'''''[[Wong Yat-fei]] \u2014 [[Shaolin Soccer]]'''''{{double-dagger}}\n**[[Patrick Tam Yiu Man|Patrick Tam]] \u2014 [[Born Wild (film)|Born Wild]] \n**[[Wai-sheung Lee|David Lee]] \u2014 [[From the Queen to the Chief Executive]] \n**[[Lam Ka-Tung]] \u2014 [[Dance of a Dream]] \n**[[Simon Yam]] \u2014 [[Midnight Fly]] \n|-\n| valign=\"top\" width=\"50%\"|\n{{Award category|#eedd82|[[Hong Kong Film Award for Best Supporting Actress|Best Supporting Actress]]}}\n*'''''[[Karena Lam]] \u2014 [[July Rhapsody]]'''''{{double-dagger}}\n**[[Josie Ho]] \u2014 [[Forever and Ever (2001 film)|Forever and Ever]] \n**[[Kara Hui]] \u2014 [[Visible Secret]] \n**[[Cecilia Yip]] \u2014 [[The Avenging Fist]] \n**[[Su Jin]] \u2014 [[Lan Yu (film)|Lan Yu]] \n| valign=\"top\" width=\"50%\"|\n{{Award category|#eedd82|[[Hong Kong Film Award for Best New Performer|Best New Performer]]}}\n*'''''[[Karena Lam]] \u2014 [[July Rhapsody]]'''''{{double-dagger}}\n**[[Niki Chow]] \u2014 [[Dummy Mommy, Without a Baby]] \n**[[Lawrence Chou]] \u2014 [[Merry-Go-Round (2001 film)|Merry-Go-Round]] \n**[[Zeny Kwok]] \u2014 [[Glass Tears (2001 film)|Glass Tears]] \n**[[Charlene Choi]] \u2014 [[Funeral March (2001 film)|Funeral March]] \n|-\n| valign=\"top\" width=\"50%\"|\n{{Award category|#eedd82|[[Hong Kong Film Award for Best Cinematography|Best Cinematography]]}}\n*'''''[[Arthur Wong]] \u2014 [[Visible Secret]]'''''{{double-dagger}}\n**[[Kwen Pak-Huen]] and [[Kwong Ting-Wo|Andy Kwong]] \u2014 [[Shaolin Soccer]] \n**[[Peter Pau]] \u2014 [[Beijing Rocks]] \n**[[Henry Chung]] \u2014 [[Peony Pavilion (2001 film)|Peony Pavilion]] \n**[[Yang Tao (cinematographer)|Yang Tao]] and [[Zhang Jian (cinematographer)|Zhang Jian]] \u2014 [[Lan Yu (film)|Lan Yu]] \n| valign=\"top\" width=\"50%\"|\n{{Award category|#eedd82|[[Hong Kong Film Award for Best Film Editing|Best Film Editing]]}}\n*'''''[[Kwong Chi-Leung|Eric Kong]] \u2014 [[The Accidental Spy]]'''''{{double-dagger}}\n**[[Kai Kit-Wai]] \u2014 [[Shaolin Soccer]] \n**[[David M. Richardson]] \u2014 [[Fulltime Killer]] \n**[[Marco Mak]] \u2014 [[The Legend of Zu]] \n**[[William Chang]] \u2014 [[Lan Yu (film)|Lan Yu]] \n|-\n| valign=\"top\" width=\"50%\"|\n{{Award category|#eedd82|[[Hong Kong Film Award for Best Art Direction|Best Art Direction]]}}\n*'''''[[Lou Zhongguo]] and [[Yan Zhanlin]] \u2014 [[Peony Pavilion (2001 film)|Peony Pavilion]]'''''{{double-dagger}}\n**[[Man Lim-Chung]] \u2014 [[July Rhapsody]] \n**[[Ho Kim-Hung|Cyrus Ho]] and [[Fu Delin]] \u2014 [[The Legend of Zu]] \n**[[Bruce Yu]] \u2014 [[Wu Yen]] \n**[[William Chang]] \u2014 [[Lan Yu (film)|Lan Yu]] \n| valign=\"top\" width=\"50%\"|\n{{Award category|#eedd82|[[Hong Kong Film Award for Best Costume Make Up Design|Best Costume Make Up Design]]}}\n*'''''[[Yeung Fan]] \u2014 [[Peony Pavilion (2001 film)|Peony Pavilion]]'''''{{double-dagger}}\n**[[Choi Yin-Man|Hilda Choi]] \u2014 [[Shaolin Soccer]] \n**[[William Fung]], [[Kwan Mei-Bo|Mabel Kwan]] and [[Lee Pik-Kwan]] <br/>\u2014 [[The Legend of Zu]] \n**[[Bruce Yu]] \u2014 [[Wu Yen]] \n**[[William Chang]] \u2014 [[Lan Yu (film)|Lan Yu]] \n|-\n| valign=\"top\" width=\"50%\"|\n{{Award category|#eedd82|[[Hong Kong Film Award for Best Action Choreography|Best Action Choreography]]}}\n*'''''[[Tung Wai]] and [[Jackie Chan Stunt Team]] \u2014 [[The Accidental Spy]]'''''{{double-dagger}}\n**[[Ching Siu-tung]] \u2014 [[Shaolin Soccer]] \n**[[Ching Siu-tung]] \u2014 [[My Schoolmate, The Barbarian]] \n**[[Corey Yuen]] \u2014 [[The Avenging Fist]] \n**[